id.name: 6-phospho-D-gluconic acid
id.definition: A gluconic acid phosphate having the phosphate group at the 6-position. It is an intermediate in the pentose phosphate pathway.

id.name: (E)-roxithromycin
id.definition: A major geometrical isomer of roxithromycin.

id.name: isobutyrate
id.definition: A branched, short-chain, saturated fatty acid anion; the conjugate base of isobutyric acid, formed by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group.

id.name: clavulanic acid
id.definition: Antibiotic isolated from Streptomyces clavuligerus. It acts as a suicide inhibitor of bacterial beta-lactamase enzymes.

id.name: L-2,4-diaminobutyric acid
id.definition: A 2,4-diaminobutyric acid that has S-configuration.

id.name: 2-phenylethanol
id.definition: A primary alcohol that is ethanol substituted by a phenyl group at position 2.

id.name: N-acetyl-L-citrulline
id.definition: The L-enantiomer of N-acetylcitrulline.

id.name: 4-phospho-D-erythronic acid
id.definition: The D-enantiomer of 4-phosphoerythronic acid.

id.name: 1-piperideine-6-carboxylic acid
id.definition: A tetrahydropyridine that is 2,3,4,5-tetrahydropyridine having a carboxy group at the 2-position.

id.name: N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminic acid
id.definition: N-Acetylneuraminic acid with alpha configuration at the anomeric centre.

id.name: 3-oxo-3-ureidopropanoic acid
id.definition: The ureido derivative of malonic acid.

id.name: N-acyl-D-glutamic acid
id.definition: An N-acyl-D-amino acid that is D-glutamic acid in which a hydrogen attached to the nitrogen has been replaced by an acyl group.

id.name: (6S,9R)-vomifoliol
id.definition: A (6S)-vomifoliol with a R configuration for the hydroxy group at position 9.

id.name: phosphatidylcholine(1+)
id.definition: A glycerophosphocholine compound having O-acyl substituents at both the 1- and 2-positions of the glycerol. It is a major constituent of cell membranes.

id.name: N(6)-carboxy-L-lysine residue
id.definition: An amino-acid residue derived from N(6)-carboxy-L-lysine.

id.name: syringaresinol
id.definition: A lignan that is 7,9':7',9-diepoxylignane substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 4 and 4' and methoxy groups at positions 3, 3', 5 and 5' respectively.

id.name: N-formyl-L-methionyl group
id.definition: An amino-acid residue derived from N-formyl-L-methionine.

id.name: anthracycline antibiotic
id.definition: An organic compound that has a tetrahydronaphthacenedione ring structure attached by a glycosidic linkage to the amino sugar daunosamine and which exhibits antibiotic activity.

id.name: dasatinib (anhydrous)
id.definition: An aminopyrimidine that is 2-methylpyrimidine which is substituted at position 4 by the primary amino group of 2-amino-1,3-thiazole-5-carboxylic acid and at position 6 by a 4-(2-hydroxyethyl)piperazin-1-yl group, and in which the carboxylic acid group has been formally condensed with 2-chloro-6-methylaniline to afford the corresponding amide. A multi-targeted kinase inhibitor, it is used, particularly as the monohydrate, for the treatment of chronic, accelerated, or myeloid or lymphoid blast phase chronic myeloid leukemia. Note that the name 'dasatinib' is used to refer to the monohydrate (USAN) as well as to anhydrous dasatinib (INN).

id.name: 3-chlorobenzoic acid
id.definition: A monochlorobenzoic acid carrying a chloro substituent at position 3.

id.name: nickel(3+)
id.definition: A nickel cation in which the nickel carries a triple positive charge.

id.name: aluminium(3+)
id.definition: An aluminium cation that has a charge of +3.

id.name: 2',6'-dichlorobiphenyl-2,3-diol
id.definition: A hydroxybiphenyl that is catechol in which the hydrogen at position 3 has been replaced by a 2,6-dichlorophenyl group.

id.name: 2'-chlorobiphenyl-2,3-diol
id.definition: A hydroxybiphenyl that is catechol in which the hydrogen at position 3 has been replaced by a 2-chlorophenyl group.

id.name: 12-bromododecanoic acid
id.definition: A bromo fatty acid consisting of lauric acid having a single bromo-substituent at the 12-position.

id.name: c-di-GMP
id.definition: A cyclic purine dinucleotide that is the 3',5'-cyclic dimer of MP.

id.name: cloxacillin
id.definition: A semisynthetic penicillin antibiotic carrying a 3-(2-chlorophenyl)-5-methylisoxazole-4-carboxamido group at position 6.

id.name: diazepam
id.definition: A 1,4-benzodiazepinone that is 1,3-dihydro-2H-1,4-benzodiazepin-2-one substituted by a chloro group at position 7, a methyl group at position 1 and a phenyl group at position 5.

id.name: 4-ethylphenol
id.definition: A member of the class of phenols carrying an ethyl substituent at position 4.

id.name: 3-chloro-L-phenylalanine
id.definition: A non-proteinogenic L-alpha-amino acid that is L-phenylalanine in which one of the meta-hydrogens of the phenyl group has been replaced by a chlorine.

id.name: Fe2S2 iron-sulfur cluster
id.definition: An iron-sulfur cluster containing two iron atoms and two sulfur atoms.

id.name: gallium atom
id.definition: A metallic element predicted as eka-aluminium by Mendeleev in 1870 and discovered by Paul-Emile Lecoq de Boisbaudran in 1875. Named in honour of France (Latin Gallia) and perhaps also from the Latin gallus cock, a translation of Lecoq.

id.name: mercury dibromide
id.definition: A mercury coordination entity composed of mercury and bromine with the formula HgBr2.

id.name: mercury diiodide
id.definition: A mercury coordination entity composed of mercury and iodine with formula HgI2.

id.name: indometacin
id.definition: A member of the class of indole-3-acetic acids that is indole-3-acetic acid in which the indole ring is substituted at positions 1, 2 and 5 by p-chlorobenzoyl, methyl, and methoxy groups, respectively. A non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug, it is used in the treatment of musculoskeletal and joint disorders including osteoarthritis, rheumatoid arthritis, gout, bursitis and tendinitis.

id.name: perchlorate
id.definition: A monovalent inorganic anion obtained by deprotonation of perchloric acid.

id.name: chlorate
id.definition: A monovalent inorganic anion obtained by deprotonation of chloric acid.

id.name: beta-D-mannose 6-phosphate
id.definition: A D-mannopyranose 6-phosphate with a beta-configuration at the anomeric position.

id.name: nickel(2+)
id.definition: A nickel cation in which the nickel carries a double positive charge.

id.name: 2,2',5,5'-tetrachloro-4,4'-bis(methylsulfonyl)biphenyl
id.definition: An member of the class of biphenyls that is 2,2',5,5'-tetrachlorobiphenyl in which the 4 and 4' positions are substituted by methylsulfonyl groups.

id.name: periodate
id.definition: A monovalent inorganic anion obtained by deprotonation of periodic acid.

id.name: tetra-mu3-sulfido-tetrairon
id.definition: An Fe4S4 iron-sulfur cluster in which each sulfur is attached to three of the iron atoms.

id.name: arsenous acid
id.definition: An arsenic oxoacid consisting of three hydroxy groups attached to a central arsenic atom.

id.name: 1,3,5-trichlorobenzene
id.definition: A trichlorobenzene carrying chloro substituents at positions 1, 3 and 5.

id.name: vandetanib
id.definition: A quinazoline that is 7-[(1-methylpiperidin-4-yl)methoxy]quinazoline bearing additional methoxy and 4-bromo-2-fluorophenylamino substituents at positions 6 and 4 respectively. Used for the treatment of symptomatic or progressive medullary thyroid cancer in patients with unresectable locally advanced or metastatic disease.

id.name: beta-pinene
id.definition: An isomer of pinene with an exocyclic double bond. It is a component of essential oils from many plants.

id.name: deoxyhypusine
id.definition: An L-lysine derivative in which the N(6) of the lysine is substituted with a 4-aminobutyl group.

id.name: (+)-alpha-thujone
id.definition: The (1R,4S,5S)-stereoisomer of alpha-thujone.

id.name: imidazolium cation
id.definition: An imidazolium ion that is the cation resulting from protonation at the 3-position of 1H-imidazole.

id.name: N-methyl-N-nitrosourea
id.definition: A member of the class of N-nitrosoureas that is urea in which one of the nitrogens is substituted by methyl and nitroso groups.

id.name: tetrasaccharide
id.definition: An oligosaccharide comprising four monomeric monosaccharide units.

id.name: monacolin L
id.definition: A polyketide that is 1-ethyl-2,6-dimethyl-1,2,6,7,8,8a-hexahydronaphthalene in which one of the methyl hydrogens from the ethyl group is replaced by a 4-hydroxy-6-ketopyran-2-yl group.

id.name: (5-hydroxyindol-3-yl)acetaldehyde
id.definition: An aldehyde that is acetaldehyde substituted by a 5-hydroxyindol-3-yl group.

id.name: retinol
id.definition: A retinoid consisting of 3,7-dimethylnona-2,4,6,8-tetraen-1-ol substituted at position 9 by a 2,6,6-trimethylcyclohex-1-en-1-yl group (geometry of the four exocyclic double bonds is not specified).

id.name: EC 3.1.4.* (phosphoric diester hydrolase) inhibitor
id.definition: An EC 3.1.* (ester hydrolase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of a phosphoric diester hydrolase (EC 3.1.4.*).

id.name: (+)-neoisodihydrocarveol
id.definition: The (1R,2S,5R)-stereoisomer of dihydrocarveol.

id.name: (+)-isodihydrocarveol
id.definition: The (1S,2S,4R)-stereoisomer of dihydrocarveol.

id.name: (+)-dihydrocarveol
id.definition: A dihydrocarveol with (1S,2S,4S)-stereochemistry.

id.name: 1-hydroxylimonen-2-one
id.definition: A limonene monoterpenoid that consists of cyclohexanone bearing hydroxy and methyl substituents at position 2 as well as an isopropenyl substituent at position 5.

id.name: 2-hydroxydicarboxylic acid
id.definition: Any dicarboxylic acid carrying a hydroxy group on the carbon atom at position alpha to the carboxy group.

id.name: dTMP residue
id.definition: The canonical deoxyribonucleotide residue formed from dTMP (5'-thymidylic acid).

id.name: podophyllotoxin
id.definition: An organic heterotetracyclic compound that has a furonaphthodioxole skeleton bearing a 3,4,5-trimethoxyphenyl substituent. It is found in the roots and rhizomes of Podophyllum species and is used for the topical treatment of genital warts.

id.name: GMP residue
id.definition: A canonical ribonucleotide residue derived from GMP.

id.name: EC 2.4.1.80 (ceramide glucosyltransferase) inhibitor
id.definition: An EC 2.4.1.* (hexosyltransferase) inhibitor that interferes with the activity of ceramide glucosyltransferase (EC 2.4.1.80).

id.name: tuberculosinyl diphosphate
id.definition: A diterpenyl phosphate that is the O-diphospho derivative of tuberculosinol.

id.name: 3',4',7-trihydroxyisoflavone
id.definition: A 7-hydroxyisoflavone that is daidzein substituted by a hydroxy group at position 3'.

id.name: 2-methylpyridine
id.definition: A methylpyridine carrying a methyl substituent at position 2.

id.name: phenprocoumon
id.definition: A hydroxycoumarin that is 4-hydroxycoumarin which is substituted at position 3 by a 1-phenylpropyl group.

id.name: 1-naphthylamine
id.definition: A naphthylamine that is naphthalene substituted by an amino group at position 1.

id.name: cis-vaccenic acid
id.definition: The cis isomer of vaccenic acid.

id.name: butyrate ester
id.definition: Any carboxylic ester where the carboxylic acid component is butyric acid.

id.name: (24R)-7alpha,24-dihydroxycholesterol
id.definition: A 7alpha,24-dihydroxycholesterol in which has R configuration at position 24.

id.name: sulfoacetic acid
id.definition: A carboxyalkanesulfonic acid that is the C-sulfo derivative of acetic acid.

id.name: butenolide
id.definition: A gamma-lactone that consists of a 2-furanone skeleton and its substituted derivatives.

id.name: nitric oxide donor
id.definition: An agent, with unique chemical structure and biochemical requirements, which generates nitric oxide.

id.name: alkyl alcohol
id.definition: An aliphatic alcohol in which the aliphatic alkane chain is substituted by a hydroxy group at unspecified position.

id.name: N(tele)-methyl-L-histidine
id.definition: A L-histidine derivative in which the methyl group is at N(tele)-position.

id.name: N(alpha)-methyl-L-histidine
id.definition: A N(alpha)-methyl-L-histidines that is L-histidine bearing a single methyl substituent at the N(alpha)-position.

id.name: precorrin-2
id.definition: The second intermediate in the biosynthesis of vitamin B12 from uroporphyrinogen III, in which methyl groups have been introduced at positions 2 and 7 of the tetrapyrrole framework.

id.name: iminoaspartic acid
id.definition: A succinic acid derivative having an imino group at the 2-position.

id.name: bone density conservation agent
id.definition: An agent that inhibits bone resorption and/or favor bone mineralization and bone regeneration. Used to heal bone fractures and to treat bone diseases such as osteopenia and osteoporosis.

id.name: 9-cis-retinoic acid
id.definition: A retinoic acid in which the exocyclic double bonds have 7E,9Z,11E,13E geometry.

id.name: carboxyacetyl group
id.definition: The univalent carboacyl group formed by loss of -OH from one of the carboxy groups of malonic acid.

id.name: N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine
id.definition: An N,N'-diacetylchitobiose having beta-configuration at the reducing end anomeric centre.

id.name: methimazole
id.definition: A member of the class of imidazoles that it imidazole-2-thione in which a methyl group replaces the hydrogen which is attached to a nitrogen.

id.name: milrinone
id.definition: A member of the class of bipyridines that is 2-pyridone which is substituted at positions 3, 5, and 6 by cyano, pyrid-4-yl, and methyl groups, respectively. It is used (particularly intravenously, as the lactate) for the short-term management of severe heart failure.

id.name: minocycline
id.definition: A tetracycline analogue having a dimethylamino group at position 7 and lacking the methyl and hydroxy groups at position 5.

id.name: oligosaccharide
id.definition: A compound in which monosaccharide units are joined by glycosidic linkages. The term is commonly used to refer to a defined structure as opposed to a polymer of unspecified length or a homologous mixture. When the linkages are of other types the compounds are regarded as oligosaccharide analogues.

id.name: 1-methylnaphthalene
id.definition: A methylnaphthalene carrying a methyl substituent at position 1.

id.name: 2-methylnaphthalene
id.definition: A methylnaphthalene carrying a methyl substituent at position 2.

id.name: (Z)-phenylacetaldehyde oxime
id.definition: A phenylacetaldehyde oxime in which the oxime moiety has Z configuration.

id.name: butanamide
id.definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide obtained by formal condensation of butanoic acid and ammonia.

id.name: mitoxantrone
id.definition: A dihydroxyanthraquinone that is 1,4-dihydroxy-9,10-anthraquinone which is substituted by 6-hydroxy-1,4-diazahexyl groups at positions 5 and 8.

id.name: calcipotriol
id.definition: A seco-cholestane that is 26,27-cyclo-9,10-secocholesta-5,7,10,22-tetraene carrying additional hydroxy substituents at positions 1, 3 and 24. It is used (as its hydrate) in combination with betamethasone dipropionate, a corticosteroid, for the topical treatment of plaque psoriasis in adult patients.

id.name: EC 5.99.1.3 [DNA topoisomerase (ATP-hydrolysing)] inhibitor
id.definition: A topoisomerase inhibitor that inhibits DNA topoisomerase (ATP-hydrolysing), EC 5.99.1.3 (also known as topoisomerase II and as DNA gyrase), which catalyses ATP-dependent breakage of both strands of DNA, passage of the unbroken strands through the breaks, and rejoining of the broken strands.

id.name: N-formyl amino acid
id.definition: Any N-acyl amino acid which has formyl as the acyl group.

id.name: N-hydroxy-alpha-amino-acid
id.definition: Any amino acid in which at least one hydrogen attached to the amino group is replaced by a hydroxy group.

id.name: (3S)-3-hydroxy-L-asparagine
id.definition: A non-proteinogenic L-alpha-amino acid that is the (3S)-hydroxy-derivative of L-asparagine.

id.name: doxycycline
id.definition: Tetracycline in which the 5beta-hydrogen is replaced by a hydroxy group, while the 6alpha-hydroxy group is replaced by hydrogen. A semi-synthetic tetracycline antibiotic, it is used to inhibit bacterial protein synthesis and treat non-gonococcal urethritis and cervicitis, exacerbations of bronchitis in patients with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), and adult periodontitis.

id.name: organic molecular entity
id.definition: Any molecular entity that contains carbon.

id.name: 3-cyclopentylpropionic acid
id.definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is propionic acid in which one of the methyl hydrogens is substituted by a cyclopentyl group.

id.name: neurotoxin
id.definition: A poison that interferes with the functions of the nervous system.

id.name: sorafenib
id.definition: A member of the class of phenylureas that is urea in which one of the nitrogens is substituted by a 4-chloro-3-trifluorophenyl group while the other is substituted by a phenyl group which, in turn, is substituted at the para position by a [2-(methylcarbamoyl)pyridin-4-yl]oxy group.

id.name: EC 2.7.11.1 (non-specific serine/threonine protein kinase) inhibitor
id.definition: An EC 2.7.11.* (protein-serine/threonine kinase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of non-specific serine/threonine protein kinase (EC 2.7.11.1), a kinase enzyme involved in phosphorylation of hydroxy group of serine or threonine.

id.name: N-acyl-Delta(8)-phytosphingenine
id.definition: Any member of the class of phytoceramides in which the sphingoid base is specified as Delta(8)-phytosphingenine.

id.name: 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA
id.definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of any 2,3-trans-enoic acid.

id.name: unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA
id.definition: A fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of any unsaturated fatty acid.

id.name: beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1-1')-Cer
id.definition: A sialotriaosylceramide consisting of the tetrasaccharide beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc attached to the primary hydroxy function of ceramide.

id.name: lucanthone
id.definition: A thioxanthen-9-one compound having a methyl substituent at the 1-position and a 2-[(diethylamino)ethyl]amino substituent at the 4-position. Formerly used for the treatment of schistosomiasis. It is a prodrug, being metabolised to hycanthone.

id.name: 3-phenylpropionate
id.definition: A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-phenylpropionic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group.

id.name: 13-sophorosyloxydocosanoate 6',6''-diacetate
id.definition: A sophorolipid that is the diacetylated sophoroside of 13-hydroxydocosanoic acid. It is a major extracellular lipid.

id.name: nitrates
id.definition: Salts or esters of nitric acid.

id.name: benzyloxycarbonyl group
id.definition: An organyl group of formula -COOCH2Ph.

id.name: pseudoephedrine
id.definition: A member of the class of the class of phenylethanolamines that is (1S)-2-(methylamino)-1-phenylethan-1-ol in which the pro-S hydrogen at position 2 is replaced by a methyl group.

id.name: SO-thioperoxol
id.definition: Organic derivatives of sulfenic acid in which the sulfeno group is linked directly to carbon.

id.name: tetraphene
id.definition: An angular ortho-fused polycyclic arene consisting of four fused benzene rings.

id.name: polyamine macromolecule
id.definition: A macromolecule composed of units connected by imino (-NR-) linkages.

id.name: penicillinate anion
id.definition: Any anion formed by loss of a proton from the carboxy group of a penicillin.

id.name: 1,3-dinitrobenzene
id.definition: A dinitrobenzene that is benzene disubstituted at positions 1 and 3 with nitro groups.

id.name: 1,4-phenylenediamine
id.definition: A phenylenediamine in which the amino functions are at positions 1 and 4 of the benzene nucleus.

id.name: N-acyl-amino acid
id.definition: A carboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of a carboxylic acid with the amino group of an amino acid.

id.name: chrysene
id.definition: An ortho-fused polycyclic arene found commonly in the coal tar.

id.name: sesquarterpenoid
id.definition: Any terpenoid derived from a sesquarterpene. The term includes compounds in which the C35 skeleton of the parent sesquarterpene has been rearranged or modified by the removal of one or more skeletal atoms (generally methyl groups).

id.name: hopanoid
id.definition: A triterpenoid based on a hopane skeleton.

id.name: chlorphenamine
id.definition: A tertiary amino compound that is propylamine which is substituted at position 3 by a pyridin-2-yl group and a p-chlorophenyl group and in which the hydrogens attached to the nitrogen are replaced by methyl groups. A histamine H1 antagonist, it is used to relieve the symptoms of hay fever, rhinitis, urticaria, and asthma.

id.name: ethoxycarbonyl group
id.definition: An organyl group of formula -COOEt.

id.name: (-)-glyceollin II
id.definition: A benzofuropyranochromene that is 3H,7H-[1]benzofuro[3,2-c]pyrano[3,2-g]chromene substituted at positions 7a and 10 by hydroxy groups and at position 3 by a gem-dimethyl group.

id.name: nile red
id.definition: An organic heterotetracyclic compound that is 5H-benzo[a]phenoxazin-5-one substituted at position 9 by a diethylamino group.

id.name: pharmaceutical
id.definition: Any substance introduced into a living organism with therapeutic or diagnostic purpose.

id.name: isothiocyanate
id.definition: An organosulfur compound with the general formula R-N=C=S.

id.name: rose bengal
id.definition: An organic potassium salt that is the dipotassium salt of 2,3,4,5-tetrachloro-6-(2,4,5,7-tetraiodo-6-hydroxy-3-oxoxanthen-9-yl)benzoic acid.

id.name: 1,2-dioleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine(1+)
id.definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups are both oleoyl.

id.name: 1-naphthaldehyde
id.definition: A naphthaldehyde with a formyl group at position 1.

id.name: 2-naphthaldehyde
id.definition: A naphthaldehyde that is naphthalene substituted by a formyl group at position 2.

id.name: N-(2-hydroxytetracosanoyl)sphinganine
id.definition: A dihydroceramide in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as 2-hydroxytetracosanoyl.

id.name: 2-arachidonoylglycerol
id.definition: An endocannabinoid and an endogenous agonist of the cannabinoid receptors (CB1 and CB2). It is an ester formed from omega-6-arachidonic acid and glycerol.

id.name: 2,5-diamino-6-(5-phosphono)ribitylamino-4(3H)-pyrimidinone
id.definition: A 1-deoxy-D-ribitol-5-phosphate having a (5,6-diamino-4-oxopyrimidin-2-yl)amino group at the 1-position.

id.name: EC 3.2.1.* (glycosidase) inhibitor
id.definition: An EC 3.2.* (glycosylase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any glycosidase (i.e. enzymes hydrolysing O- and S-glycosyl compounds, EC 3.2.1.*).

id.name: 6-(alpha-D-glucosaminyl)-1D-myo-inositol 1,2-cyclic phosphate
id.definition: A myo-inositol cyclic phosphate that is 1D-myo-inositol 1,2-cyclic phosphate having an alpha-D-glucosaminyl residue attached at the 6-position.

id.name: 5-oxo-ETE
id.definition: An oxoicosatetraenoic acid having a 5-oxo group; and (6E)-, (8Z), (11Z)- and (14Z)-double bonds.

id.name: 2-O-acetyl-1-O-octadecyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A 2-acetyl-1-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine betaine which has octadecyl as the alkyl group. PAF is a potent phospholipid activator and mediator of many leukocyte functions, including platelet aggregation, inflammation, and anaphylaxis.

id.name: 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine
id.definition: An sn-glycerophosphoserine compound having an acyl substituent at the 1-hydroxy position.

id.name: N-acylsphingosine
id.definition: The parent compounds of the ceramide family, composed of sphingosine having an unspecified fatty acyl group attached to the nitrogen.

id.name: N-acylethanolamine
id.definition: An ethanolamine substituted at nitrogen by an acyl group.

id.name: bepridil hydrochloride monohydrate
id.definition: The hydrochloride monohydrate of bepridril.

id.name: bortezomib
id.definition: L-Phenylalaninamide substituted at the amide nitrogen by a 1-(dihydroxyboranyl)-3-methylbutyl group and at N(alpha) by a pyrazin-2-ylcarbonyl group. It is a dipeptidyl boronic acid that reversibly inhibits the 26S proteasome.

id.name: alpha-D-glucosiduronic acid
id.definition: A glucosiduronic acid in which the glucuronic moiety has alpha-D stereochemistry.

id.name: C3-oxacyanine
id.definition: A C3 cyanine dye having 3-ethyl-1,3-benzoxazol-2(3H)-yl units at each end.

id.name: Delta(11)-fatty acyl-CoA
id.definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of any Delta(11)-fatty acid.

id.name: Delta(12)-fatty acyl-CoA
id.definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of any Delta(12)-fatty acid.

id.name: 5,6-bis(diphospho)-1D-myo-inositol tetrakisphosphate
id.definition: A 1D-myo-inositol bis(diphosphate) tetrakisphosphate having the two diphospho groups located at positions 5 and 6.

id.name: (S)-3-hydroxyhexacosanoyl-CoA
id.definition: A very long-chain hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (S)-3-hydroxyhexacosanoic acid.

id.name: 3-oxohexacosanoyl-CoA
id.definition: A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-oxohexacosanoic acid.

id.name: N-tetracosanoylphytosphingosine
id.definition: A phytoceramide compound having a tetracosanoyl group attached to the nitrogen atom.

id.name: N-hexacosanoylphytosphingosine
id.definition: A phytoceramide compound having a hexacosanoyl group attached to the nitrogen atom.

id.name: 4,6-dideoxy-4-(3-deoxy-L-glycero-tetronamido)-alpha-D-Manp2Me-(1->2)-4,6-dideoxy-4-(3-deoxy-L-glycero-tetronamido)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->2)-4,6-dideoxy-4-(3-deoxy-L-glycero-tetronamido)-alpha-D-Manp
id.definition: An amido trisaccharide fragment which mimicks the terminus of the O-polysaccharide of Vibrio cholerae O:1, serotype Ogawa.

id.name: lormetazepam
id.definition: A 1,4-benzodiazepinone compound having a methyl substituent at the 1-position, a hydroxy substituent at the 3-position, a 2-chlorophenyl group at the 5-position and a chloro substituent at the 7-position.

id.name: 3'-CMP
id.definition: A cytidine 3'-phosphate compound with a monophosphate group at the 3'-position.

id.name: 4-deoxy-4-formamido-alpha-L-arabinopyranosyl ditrans,polycis-undecaprenyl phosphate
id.definition: A polyprenyl glycosyl phosphate consisting of 4-deoxy-4-formamido-alpha-L-arabinopyranose attached at the 1-position to di-trans,poly-cis-undecaprenyl phosphate.

id.name: aflatoxin B1 triol
id.definition: An organic heterotricyclic compound obtained by oxidative cleavage of the furofuran ring system of aflatoxin B1.

id.name: pristane
id.definition: A norterpene that is an acyclic saturated hydrocarbon derived from phytane by loss of its C-16 terminal methyl group.

id.name: verapamil hydrochloride
id.definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of dexverapamil hydrochloride and (S)-verapamil hydrochloride.

id.name: O-propanoyl-L-carnitine
id.definition: An optically active O-acylcarnitine compound having propanoyl as the acyl substituent and (R)-configuration at the 3-position.

id.name: copolymer macromolecule
id.definition: A macromolecule derived from two or more species of monomer.

id.name: gamma-poly(D-glutamic acid) macromolecule
id.definition: A biomacromolecule comprised of repeating D-glutamic acid residues linked by peptidic bonds between the amino and gamma-carboxy groups.

id.name: polysorbate 80
id.definition: A polymer composed of PEG-ylated sorbitan, where the total number of poly(ethylene glycol) units is 20 (w + x + y + z = 20) and a single terminal is capped by an oleoyl group.

id.name: alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-[beta-D-Xylp-(1->2)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)]-D-GlcpNAc
id.definition: A branched heptasaccharide derivative consisting of a D-GlcNAc residue at the reducing end with a D-Man-alpha(1->6)-[D-Xyl-beta(1->2)-D-Man-alpha(1->3)]-D-Man-beta(1->4)-GlcNAc moiety attached via a beta-(1->4)-linkage and an L-Fuc residue attached via an alpha-(1->3)-linkage.

id.name: all-cis-icosa-8,11,14-trienoic acid
id.definition: An icosatrienoic acid having three cis double bonds at positions 8, 11 and 14.

id.name: poly(L-arginine) macromolecule
id.definition: A macromolecule composed of repeating L-arginyl units joined via peptide linkages.

id.name: N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl-L-serine residue
id.definition: An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl-L-serine.

id.name: O-(N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl)-L-serine
id.definition: A non-proteinogenic L-amino acid that is N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine linked via an alpha glycosidic bond to the O at position 3 of L-serine.

id.name: 3,5-dinitrosalicylic acid
id.definition: A monohydroxybenzoic acid consisting of 2-hydroxybenzoic acid having nitro substituents at the 3- and 5-positions. It is used in colorimetric testing for the presence of free carbonyl groups (C=O) in reducing sugars.

id.name: alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-D-galactose
id.definition: A glycosylgalactose comprising two D-galactose units joined via an alpha-(1->3) linkage.

id.name: biguanides
id.definition: A class of oral hypoglycemic drugs used for diabetes mellitus or prediabetes treatment. They have a structure based on the 2-carbamimidoylguanidine skeleton.

id.name: sodium amidotrizoate
id.definition: The sodium salt of a benzoic acid having iodo substituents at the 2-, 4- and 6-positions and acetamido substituents at the 3- and 5-positions. It is used, often as a mixture with the meglumine salt, as an X-ray contrast medium in gastrointestinal studies, angiography, and urography.

id.name: divinyl sulfone
id.definition: A sulfone compound having two S-vinyl substituents.

id.name: acenocoumarol
id.definition: A hydroxycoumarin that is warfarin in which the hydrogen at position 4 of the phenyl substituent is replaced by a nitro group.

id.name: almitrine dimesylate
id.definition: The dimethanesulfonate salt of almitrine.

id.name: dibenzooxazepine
id.definition: An organic heterotricyclic compound consisting of two benzene rings fused to a seven-membered ring containing one oxygen and one nitrogen atom.

id.name: mu-opioid receptor agonist
id.definition: A compound that exhibits agonist activity at the mu-opioid receptor.

id.name: isoxazoles
id.definition: Oxazoles in which the N and O atoms are adjacent.

id.name: ferriheme b(1-)
id.definition: Ferriheme b carrying an overall charge of -1, caused by loss of a proton from each of the two carboxy groups.

id.name: p-nitrophenylphosphocholine
id.definition: A phosphocholine that is the 4-nitrophenyl ester of choline phosphate.

id.name: beta-GlcNAc-(1->4)-MurNAc-L-Ala-gamma-D-Glu-L-Lys-(D-Ala)2
id.definition: An N-acetyl-beta-D-glycosaminyl glycopeptide consisting of an N-acetyl-beta-D-glycosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetylmuramoyl moiety attached to the amino terminus of the pentapeptide L-Ala-gamma-D-Glu-L-Lys-D-Ala-D-Ala via an amide linkage.

id.name: 1-O-hexadecyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A 1-O-alkyl-2-O-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine where the alkyl group is specified as hexadecyl.

id.name: 2-demethylmenaquinol
id.definition: A polyprenylnaphthohydroquinone that is naphthalene-1,4-diol having a polyprenyl substituent of unspecified chain-length at the 2-position.

id.name: alpha-phenylglycine
id.definition: An amino acid with a structure in which a phenyl ring is bonded to the alpha-carbon of glycine.

id.name: 2-amino-4-hydroxypyrimidine
id.definition: An aminopyrimidine in which the pyrimidine ring bears amino and hydroxy substituents at positions 2 and 4, respectively.

id.name: methyl alpha-D-galactoside
id.definition: An alpha-D-galactoside having a methyl substituent at the anomeric position.

id.name: thymidine 3'-monophosphate
id.definition: A pyrimidine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside 3'-monophosphate having thymine as the nucleobase.

id.name: 5-(2-carboxylatoethyl)-4-oxo-4,5-dihydro-1H-imidazol-5-ide
id.definition: Conjugate base of 3-(4-oxo-4,5-dihydro-1H-imidazol-5-yl)propanoic acid.

id.name: 2-amino-5-formylamino-6-(1-D-ribosylamino)pyrimidin-4(3H)-one 5'-phosphate(2-)
id.definition: The dianion obtained by removal of the two acidic protons from the phosphate group of 2-amino-5-formylamino-6-(1-D-ribosylamino)pyrimidin-4(3H)-one 5'-phosphate.

id.name: 3-sn-phosphatidyl-L-serine(1-)
id.definition: A singly-charged anionic phospholipid that is the conjugate base of 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine, in which the carboxy and phosphate groups are anionic and the amino group is cationic; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: (9Z,13S)-12,13-epoxyoctadeca-9,11-dienoate
id.definition: A long-chain unsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (9Z,13S)-12,13-epoxyoctadeca-9,11-dienoic acid arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function.

id.name: long-chain fatty acid anion
id.definition: A fatty acid anion with a chain length of C13 or greater.

id.name: N(6)-(1,2-dicarboxylatoethyl)-AMP(4-)
id.definition: Tetraanion of N(6)-(1,2-dicarboxyethyl)-AMP arising from deprotonation of carboxylic acid and phosphate functions.

id.name: UDP-alpha-D-xylose(2-)
id.definition: Dianion of UDP-alpha-D-xylose arising from deprotonation of both free diphosphate OH groups.

id.name: 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: The conjugate base of a 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine compound formed by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group.

id.name: chlorogenate
id.definition: A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of chlorogenic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: dTDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxy-alpha-D-glucose(2-)
id.definition: Dianion of dTDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxy-alpha-D-glucose arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3. It is an intermediate in dTDP-rhamnose biosynthesis.

id.name: 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4-bisphosphate(5-)
id.definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained via global deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4-bisphosphate.

id.name: oxalurate
id.definition: The conjugate base of oxaluric acid; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,5-bisphosphate(5-)
id.definition: The pentaanion of a 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,5-bisphosphate.

id.name: 1-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-)
id.definition: Dianion of a 1-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate arising from deprotonation of both phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: 3-phosphoglycerate(3-)
id.definition: Trianion of 3-phosphoglyceric acid arising from deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate groups; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: nucleoside 5'-monophosphate(2-)
id.definition: The dianion of a nucleoside monophosphate: major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-gamma-D-glutamyl-L-lysyl-D-alanyl-D-alanine(3-)
id.definition: Trianion of UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-gamma-D-glutamyl-L-lysyl-D-alanyl-D-alanine(3-) arising from deprotonation of diphosphate and carboxy groups and protonation of the side-chain amino group of the lysyl residue; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: (2S)-2-hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion
id.definition: A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion where the hydroxy group is placed at position 2 (alpha to the carboxy group) and has (S)-stereochemistry; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: 1-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: The ammonium betaine of a 1-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4-phosphate(3-)
id.definition: An organophosphate oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol-4-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: 1-acyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine betaine
id.definition: The ammonium betaine formed from 1-acyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group.

id.name: 2-oxophytanate
id.definition: Conjugate base of 2-oxophytanic acid.

id.name: 1-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)-ATP(6-)
id.definition: Hexaanion of 1-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)-ATP.

id.name: 1-(sn-glycero-3-O-phosphonato)-1D-myo-inositol
id.definition: An inositol phosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the free phosphate OH group of 1-(sn-glycero-3-phospho)-1D-myo-inositol; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: 4-(phosphonatooxy)-L-threonine(2-)
id.definition: Conjugate base of 4-(phosphonooxy)-L-threonine.

id.name: 5-amino-6-(5-phospho-D-ribosylamino)uracil(2-)
id.definition: The dianion resulting from the removal of two protons from the phosphate group of 5-amino-6-(5-phospho-D-ribosylamino)uracil.

id.name: kynurenate
id.definition: A quinolinemonocarboxylate that is the conjugate base of kynurenic acid

id.name: 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-bisphosphate(5-)
id.definition: The pentaanion of a 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-bisphosphate.

id.name: gibberellin A1(1-)
id.definition: Conjugate base of gibberellin A1.

id.name: gibberellin A20(1-)
id.definition: Conjugate base of gibberellin A20.

id.name: cob(II)yrinic acid a,c diamide(4-)
id.definition: A precorrin carboxylic acid anion obtained by global deprotonation of the carboxy groups of cob(II)yrinic acid a,c diamide. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

id.name: gibberellin A44(1-)
id.definition: Conjugate base of gibberellin A44.

id.name: cob(I)yrinate a,c diamide(5-)
id.definition: A precorrin carboxylic acid anion obtained by global deprotonation of the carboxy groups of cob(I)yrinate a,c diamide. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

id.name: gibberellin A19(2-)
id.definition: Dicarboxylate anion of gibberellin A19.

id.name: gibberellin A8(1-)
id.definition: Conjugate base of gibberellin A8.

id.name: N(4)-{beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc}-Asn zwitterion
id.definition: Zwitterionic form of N(4)-{N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->3)-[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->6)]-beta-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl}-L-asparagine.

id.name: N(4)-{N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->3)-[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->6)]-beta-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->3)]-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl}-L-asparagine zwitterion
id.definition: Zwitterionic form of N(4)-{N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->3)-[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->6)]-beta-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->3)]-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl}-L-asparagine.

id.name: N(4)-{N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->3)-[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->6)]-beta-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->6)]-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl}-L-asparagine zwitterion
id.definition: Zwitterionic form of N(4)-{N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->3)-[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->6)]-beta-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->6)]-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl}-L-asparagine.

id.name: S-substituted L-cysteine zwitterion
id.definition: The zwitterionic form of an S-substituted L-cysteine.

id.name: S-substituted N-acetyl-L-cysteinate
id.definition: A sulfur-containing amino-acid anion arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid function of any S-substituted N-acetyl-L-cysteine.

id.name: 2-aminobut-2-enoate
id.definition: Conjugate base of 2-aminobut-2-enoic acid.

id.name: N-acetyl-L-citrullinate
id.definition: An N-acyl-L-alpha-amino acid anion that is the conjugate base of N-acetyl-L-citrulline, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: (S)-1-piperideine-6-carboxylate
id.definition: An optically active form of 1-piperideine-6-carboxylate having (S)-configuration.

id.name: 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA(4-)
id.definition: An acyl-CoA(4-) oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of any 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: 4-deoxy-4-formamido-alpha-L-arabinopyranosyl ditrans,polycis-undecaprenyl phosphate(1-)
id.definition: Conjugate base of 4-deoxy-4-formamido-alpha-L-arabinopyranosyl di-trans,poly-cis-undecaprenyl phosphate arising from deprotonation of the free OH group of the phosphate.

id.name: neohesperidin
id.definition: A flavanone glycoside that is hesperitin having an 2-O-(alpha-L-rhamnopyranosyl)-beta-D-glucopyranosyl moiety attached to the 7-hydroxy group.

id.name: alpha-methyltryptamine
id.definition: A tryptamine derivative having a methyl substituent at the alpha-position.

id.name: alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc
id.definition: A branched amino tetrasaccharide consisting of N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine at the reducing end having an alpha-L-fucosyl residue attached at the 3-position and an alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-galactosyl moiety attached at the 4-position. A cancer-associated tetrasaccharide antigen which constitutes the core structure recognised by therapeutic antibody BR96. Conformational restriction around the GlcNAc residue is a key feature of its structure.

id.name: dimethyl sulfate
id.definition: The dimethyl ester of sulfuric acid.

id.name: diethyl pyrocarbonate
id.definition: The diethyl ester of dicarbonic acid.

id.name: EC 3.4.24.* (metalloendopeptidase) inhibitor
id.definition: Any EC 3.4.* (hydrolases acting on peptide bond) inhibitor that interferes with the activity of a metalloendopeptidase (EC 3.4.24.*).

id.name: 3-pentadecylcatechol
id.definition: Catechol substituted at position 3 with a pentadecyl group.

id.name: N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucose
id.definition: An amino trisaccharide that is the carbohydrate portion of ganglioside GM3. It comprises a linear sequence of alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl, beta-D-galactosyl and beta-D-glucose residues linked (2->3) and (1->4).

id.name: 4,6-dideoxy-4-(3-deoxy-L-glycero-tetronamido)-alpha-D-Manp2Me-(1->2)-4,6-dideoxy-4-(3-deoxy-L-glycero-tetronamido)-alpha-D-ManpOMe
id.definition: An amido disaccharide fragment which mimicks the terminus of the O-polysaccharide of Vibrio cholerae O:1, serotype Ogawa.
An amido pentasaccharide fragment which mimicks the terminus of the O-polysaccharide of Vibrio cholerae O:1, serotype Ogawa.

id.name: methylammonium
id.definition: The conjugate acid of methylamine; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: 4,6-(1'-carboxyethylidene)-3-O-methyl-beta-D-glucopyranose
id.definition: A monosaccharide derivative that is beta-D-glucopyranose having a methyl group at the 3-position and a 1-carboxyethylidene group masking the 4-and 6-positions.

id.name: alpha-D-GalpNAc-(1->2)-alpha-DD-Hepp-(1->6)-alpha-D-GlcpN
id.definition: A linear amino trisaccharide consisting of N-acetyl-alpha-glucosamine, alpha-glycero-alpha-D-manno-heptose and alpha-glucosamine residues linked (1->2) and (1->6) respectively.

id.name: muramyl dipeptide
id.definition: Muramyl dipeptide is a peptidoglycan constituent of both Gram positive and Gram negative bacteria. It is composed of N-acetylmuramic acid linked by its lactic acid moiety to the N-terminus of the dipeptide L-alanyl-D-isoglutamine.

id.name: N(4)-{N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->3)-[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->6)]-[beta-D-xylosyl-(1->2)]-beta-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl}-L-asparagine zwitterion
id.definition: An amino acid zwitterion that is the zwitterionic form of N(4)-{N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->3)-[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl-(1->6)]-[beta-D-xylosyl-(1->2)]-beta-D-mannosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl}-L-asparagine.

id.name: N-[(R)-4-phosphonatopantothenoyl]-L-cysteinate(3-)
id.definition: Trianion of N-[(R)-4-phosphopantothenoyl]-L-cysteine arising from deprotonation of carboxylic acid and phosphate functions.

id.name: 2-hydroxy-5-(methylsulfanyl)-3-oxopent-1-enyl phosphate(2-)
id.definition: Dianion of 2-hydroxy-5-(methylsulfanyl)-3-oxopent-1-en-1-yl phosphate.

id.name: monodehydro-L-ascorbate(1-)
id.definition: The conjugate base of monodehydro-L-ascorbic acid arising from deprotonation of the 4-hydroxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: (4Z)-2,8:7,12:11,15:14,18:17,22-pentaanhydro-4,5,6,9,10,13,19,20,21-nonadeoxy-L-arabino-L-allo-L-allo-docosa-4,9,20-trienitol
id.definition: A trans-fused organic heteropentacyclic compound consisting of an oxacyclooctene, an oxepane, two pyrans and a further oxepane ring fused in a linear sequence.

id.name: sapropterin
id.definition: A tetrahydropterin that is 2-amino-5,6,7,8-tetrahydropteridin-4(3H)-one in which a hydrogen at position 6 is substituted by a 1,2-dihydroxypropyl group (6R,1'R,2'S-enantiomer).

id.name: (1->2)-beta-D-mannan
id.definition: A mannan consisting of repeating mannosyl units joined via beta-(1->2)-linkages.

id.name: alpha-D-Galp-(1->2)-[alpha-D-Abep-(1->3)]-alpha-D-Manp-(1->4)-alpha-L-Rhap-(1->3)-alpha-D-Galp-(1->2)-[alpha-D-Abep-(1->3)]-alpha-D-Manp-(1->4)-alpha-L-Rhap-(1->3)-alpha-D-Galp-(1->2)-[alpha-D-Abep-(1->3)]-alpha-D-Manp-(1->4)-alpha-L-Rhap
id.definition: A polysaccharide that is a branched dodecasaccharide consisting of three repeating tetrasaccharide units; reported to be a possible epitope of the O-antigen polysaccharide in Salmonella.

id.name: (R)-cyclopentolate hydrochloride
id.definition: The hydrochloride salt of (R)-cyclopentolate.

id.name: N-methylglucamine
id.definition: A hexosamine that is D-glucitol in which the hydroxy group at position 1 is substituted by the nitrogen of a methylamino group. A crystalline base, it is used in preparing salts of certain acids for use as diagnostic radiopaque media, while its antimonate is used as an antiprotozoal in the treatment of leishmaniasis.

id.name: cromoglycic acid
id.definition: A dicarboxylic acid that is the bis-chromone derivative of glycerol. It is effective as a mast cell stabilizer.

id.name: 3',5'-di-O-methyltricetin
id.definition: The 3',5'-di-O-methyl ether of tricetin. Known commonly as tricin, it is a constituent of rice bran and has been found to potently inhibit colon cancer cell growth.

id.name: 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-diphosphate(3-)
id.definition: Trianion of 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-diphosphate arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups.

id.name: L-proline zwitterion
id.definition: The zwitterion formed from L-proline by proton transfer from the carboxy group to the ring nitrogen. It is the predominant species at physiological pH.

id.name: N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-1-diphospho-ditrans,polycis-undecaprenol(2-)
id.definition: The dianion resulting from the removal of two protons from the diphosphate group of N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-1-diphospho-ditrans,polycis-undecaprenol.

id.name: dermatan anion
id.definition: A carbohydrate acid derivative anion obtained from dermatan by deprotonation of the carboxylic acid groups of the repeating units; the major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-2,3-beta-D-galactosyl-1,3-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl group(1-)
id.definition: Conjugate base of the alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-2,3-beta-D-galactosyl-1,3-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl group arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: N(6)-(1-carboxyethyl)-L-lysine
id.definition: A L-lysine derivative formed during the reaction between methylglyoxal and protein. CEL is a homologue of N(epsilon)-(carboxymethyl)lysine (CML), an advanced glycation end-product that is formed on reaction of glyoxal or glycolaldehyde with protein and on oxidative cleavage of fructoselysine, the Amadori adduct formed on glycation of protein by glucose.

id.name: 5-hydroxylysine
id.definition: A hydroxylysine that is lysine substituted by a hydroxy group at position 5.

id.name: alpha-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-D-Gal
id.definition: A trisaccharide consisting of three D-galactosyl residues connected via sequential alpha-(1->3)- and beta-(1->4)-linkages.

id.name: alpha-D-Galp-(1->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-alpha-D-Galp-(1->3)-D-Galp
id.definition: A tetrasaccharide comprised of four D-galactose residues connected sequentially by alpha(1->3), beta(1->4) and alpha(1->3) linkages.

id.name: alpha-D-Galp-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)]-D-Galp
id.definition: A branched trisaccharide consisting of D-galactose having an alpha-L-fucosyl residue at the 2-position and an alpha-D-galactosyl residue at the 3-position.

id.name: inositol phosphoceramide
id.definition: A phosphosphingolipid in which an inositol residue and the ceramide moiety are linked via a phosphodiester bridge. The ceramide moiety contains substituents R(1) and R(2) which vary with different sphingoid bases and fatty acyl moieties.

id.name: EC 3.4.* (hydrolases acting on peptide bond) inhibitor
id.definition: A hydrolase inhibitor that interferes with the action of any hydrolase acting on peptide bonds (peptidase), EC 3.4.*.*).

id.name: N(omega)-(ADP-D-ribosyl)-L-arginine(1-)
id.definition: A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion that is the conjugate base of N(omega)-(ADP-D-ribosyl)-L-arginine; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: iron-sulfur-vanadium cofactor
id.definition: A 7Fe-V-9S-X-homocitryl cluster, the structure of which is assumed to be analogous to the 7Fe-Mo-9S-X-homocitryl cluster. The identity of the X atom is not known, possibly carbon or oxygen.

id.name: CMP(2-)
id.definition: A nucleoside 5'-monophosphate(2-) that results from the removal of two protons from the phosphate group of CMP; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: magnesium 13(1)-hydroxyprotoporphyrin 13-monomethyl ester(1-)
id.definition: The conjugate base of magnesium 13(1)-hydroxyprotoporphyrin 13-monomethyl ester, formed by deprotonation of the carboxyethyl group at C-17. It is the principal species at pH 7.3.

id.name: magnesium 13(1)-oxoprotoporphyrin 13-monomethyl ester(1-)
id.definition: The conjugate base of magnesium 13(1)-oxoprotoporphyrin 13-monomethyl ester, formed by deprotonation of the carboxyethyl group at C-17. It is the principal species at pH 7.3.

id.name: magnesium protoporphyrin 13-monomethyl ester(1-)
id.definition: The conjugate base of magnesium protoporphyrin 13-monomethyl ester, formed by deprotonation of the carboxyethyl group at C-17. It is the principal species at pH 7.3.

id.name: 1-alkyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion
id.definition: An alkyl,acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which unspecified alkyl and acyl groups are located at positions 1 and 2 respectively.

id.name: phosphatidylglycerol phosphate(3-)
id.definition: The glycerophosphoglycerophosphate anion of charge -3 formed by loss of a 3 protons from the OH groups of the phosphate functions.

id.name: ferroheme o(2-)
id.definition: The cyclic tetrapyrrole anion that is ferroheme o protonated to pH 7.3.

id.name: gamma-poly(D-glutamic acid) polymer
id.definition: A gamma-poly(glutamic acid) polymer, composed of gamma-poly(D-glutamic acid) macromolecules.

id.name: bicozamycin
id.definition: A commercially important azabicyclic antibiotic obtained from Streptomyces sapporonensis. It inhibits the Rho protein of E. coli.

id.name: N(4)-{alpha-D-Glc-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc}-Asn residue
id.definition: An N(4)-glycosylated asparagine residue in which the glycan moiety is a branched undecasaccharide consisting of one D-glucosyl residue, eight D-mannosyl residues and two N-acetylglucosamine residues, one of which at the reducing end is bonded to the asparagine N(4) atom.

id.name: lefradafiban
id.definition: A member of the class of pyrrolidin-2-ones that is pyrrolidin-2-one in which the 3-pro-S-hydrogen is substituted by a 2-methoxy-2-oxoethyl group, while the 5-pro-S-hydrogen is substituted by a ({4'-[N-(methoxycarbonyl)carbamimidoyl]biphenyl-4-yl}oxy)methyl group. It is an orally active prodrug of fradafiban, a figrinogen receptor antagonist.

id.name: (+)-(1R)-1-[4-(4-fluorophenyl)-2,6-diisopropyl-5-propylpyridin-3-yl]ethanol
id.definition: A 4-aryl-5-(2-hydroxyalkyl)pyridine derivative used as a glucagon receptor antagonist.

id.name: NMDA receptor antagonist
id.definition: Any substance that inhibits the action of N-methyl-D-aspartate (NMDA) receptors. They tend to induce a state known as dissociative anesthesia, marked by catalepsy, amnesia, and analgesia, while side effects can include hallucinations, nightmares, and confusion. Due to their psychotomimetic effects, many NMDA receptor antagonists are used as recreational drugs.

id.name: 2-hydroxy-3-methylbutyric acid
id.definition: A valine derivative that is valine in which the amino group has been replaced by a hydroxy group.

id.name: valproate
id.definition: A branched-chain saturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of valproic acid.

id.name: 1,2-di-O-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are both arachidonoyl.

id.name: (2S,3S)-2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid
id.definition: A 2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid in which both stereocentres have S-configuration.

id.name: 5-HETE
id.definition: A HETE having a 5-hydroxy group and (6E)-, (8Z)-, (11Z)- and (14Z)-double bonds.

id.name: alpha-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-D-Glc
id.definition: A linear trisaccharide comprising D-glucose (at the reducing end) having an alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl moiety at the 4-position.

id.name: alkylphosphonate
id.definition: An organic phosphonate containing a C-PO(OH)2 or C-PO(OR)2 group (where R = alkyl group).

id.name: Ac-Cha-Gpg-Disc-Nle-NMeBn
id.definition: A synthetic tetrapeptide composed of the non-natural Ac-Cha, Gpg, Disc and Nle-NMeBn residues coupled in sequence.

id.name: 1-hexadecanoyl-2-(9-oxononanoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as hexadecanoyl and 9-oxononanoyl respectively.

id.name: tacrolimus (anhydrous)
id.definition: Tacrolimus is a macrolide containing a 23-membered lactone ring, originally isolated from the fermentation broth of a Japanese soil sample that contained the bacteria Streptomyces tsukubaensis.

id.name: romidepsin
id.definition: A cyclodepsipeptide consisting of the cyclic disulfide of (2Z)-2-aminobut-2-enoyl, L-valyl, (3S,4E)-3-hydroxy-7-sulfanylhept-4-enoyl, D-valyl and D-cysteinyl residues coupled in sequence and cyclised head-to tail.

id.name: 4-nitrophenyl phosphate(2-)
id.definition: An organophosphate oxoanion that results from the removal of two protons from the phosphate group of 4-nitrophenyl phosphate.

id.name: ferroheme d1
id.definition: A ferroheme having four carboxy groups and oxo groups on two of the pyrrole rings.

id.name: succinylcholine chloride (anhydrous)
id.definition: A chloride salt in which the negative charge of the chloride ions is balanced by succinylcholine dications.

id.name: (beta-D-glucopyranosyloxymethyl)deoxyuridine 5'-monophosphate residue
id.definition: A deoxyribonucleotide residue in which a 5-hydroxymethyluracil residue is glycosidically linked via the 5-hydroxymethyl oxygen to beta-D-glucose.

id.name: UDP-3-O-[(3R)-3-hydroxytetradecanoyl]-D-glucosamine(1-)
id.definition: A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups and protonation of the amino group of UDP-3-O-[(3R)-3-hydroxytetradecanoyl]-D-glucosamine.

id.name: dihydroxyphenylacetic acid
id.definition: A dihydroxy monocarboxylic acid consisting of phenylacetic acid having two phenolic hydroxy substituents.

id.name: gamma-poly(glutamate) polymer
id.definition: An ionic polymer, composed of gamma-poly(glutamate) macromolecules (D and/or L-glutamate residues linked by gamma-peptidyl bonds).

id.name: isopropyl beta-D-thiogalactopyranoside
id.definition: An S-glycosyl compound consisting of beta-D-1-thiogalactose having an isopropyl group attached to the anomeric sulfur.

id.name: beta-D-ManNAcA-(1->4)-alpha-D-GlcNAc-1-diphospho-ditrans,polycis-undecaprenol
id.definition: A polyprenyl phospho oligosaccharide where beta-D-ManNAcA-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc comprises the oligosaccharide component and is linked via a diphosphate to a polyprenyl chain consisting of eleven prenyl units.

id.name: alpha-L-Fuc-(1->2)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1-1')-Cer
id.definition: A glycopentaosylceramide having alpha-L-Fuc-(1->2)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the glycopentaosyl component.

id.name: beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1-1')-Cer
id.definition: A glycohexaosylceramide having beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the glycohexaosyl component.

id.name: L-prolylglycine
id.definition: A dipeptide consisting of glycine having an L-prolyl group attached to its alpha-amino nitrogen.

id.name: dec-2-enal
id.definition: A decenal in which the C=C bond is located at the 2-3 position.

id.name: 5-methyl-dCTP
id.definition: A 2'-deoxycytidine phosphate having 5-methylcytosine as the nucleobase.

id.name: beta-D-galactopyranosyl diglyceride
id.definition: A galactosylglycerol derivative consisting of a 1,2-diglyceride having a beta-D-galactosyl residue attached at the 3-position.

id.name: beta-D-Gal-(1->3-)-alpha-D-GalNAc
id.definition: An amino disaccharide composed of D-galactose and N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl residues in beta-(1->3) linkage.

id.name: [8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->9)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->]n
id.definition: A polysaccharide derivative composed of repeating sialyl residues connected by alternating (2->8) and (2->9) linkages.

id.name: 2,3-dipalmitoyl-S-glycerylcysteine
id.definition: An L-cysteine thioether that is L-cysteine in which the hydrogen of the thiol group is substituted by a 2,3-bis(palmitoyloxy)propyl group.

id.name: 3-sulfino-L-alanine residue
id.definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue derived from 3-sulfino-L-alanine.

id.name: 2-cis-abscisate
id.definition: A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of cis-abscisic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neup5Ac
id.definition: alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-Neu5Ac in which the configuration at the anomeric carbon atom of the residue at the reducing end is alpha

id.name: beta-D-glucosyl-N-(docosanoyl)sphingosine
id.definition: A beta-D-glucosylceramide where the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as docosanoyl.

id.name: N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl group
id.definition: An N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl group having beta-configuration at its point of attachment and an N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl residue attached at the 4-position via a beta-linkage.

id.name: 2-(beta-D-glucosyloxy)-cis-cinnamate
id.definition: A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-(beta-D-glucosyl)oxy-cis-cinnamic acid; major species ar pH 7.3.

id.name: UDP-2-acetamido-3-ammonio-2,3-dideoxy-alpha-D-glucuronate(2-)
id.definition: A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion obtained via deprotonation of the diphosphate and carboxy OH groups and protonation of the primary amino group of UDP-2-acetamido-3-amino-2,3-dideoxy-alpha-D-glucuronic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: UDP-2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-ribo-hex-3-uluronate(3-)
id.definition: A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion obtained via deprotonation of the diphosphate and carboxy OH groups of UDP-2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-ribo-hex-3-uluronic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: alectinib hydrochloride
id.definition: A hydrochloride obtained by combining alectinib with one molar equivalent of hydrochloric acid. Used for the treatment of patients with anaplastic lymphoma kinase-positive, metastatic non-small cell lung cancer.

id.name: propanoyl-AMP
id.definition: A purine ribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate consisting of adenosine 5'-monophosphate where one of the hydroxy groups of the phosphate has been condensed with propionic acid.

id.name: (17Z)-protosta-17(20),24-dien-3beta-ol
id.definition: A 3beta-hydroxy steroid having an ent-dammarane skeleton with a double bond at C-24 and a Z-double bond at C-17(20).

id.name: sphingomyelin d18:1(1+)
id.definition: A quaternary ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of sphingomyelin d18:1, obtined by protonation of the anionic phosphate function.

id.name: (S)-3-hydroxyisobutyrate
id.definition: The hydroxy fatty acid anion that is formed by loss of a proton from the carboxy group of (S)-3-hydroxyisobutyric acid.

id.name: neoflavans
id.definition: Any neoflavonoid with a 3,4-dihydro-4-aryl-2H-1-benzopyran skeleton and its substituted derivatives.

id.name: estra-1,3,5(10)-trien-3-ol
id.definition: A 3-hydroxy steroid resulting from deoxygenation at position 17 of estradiol or estrone.

id.name: 4-hydroxy-17beta-estradiol
id.definition: A 4-hydroxy steroid that consists of 17beta-estradiol having an additional hydroxy group at position 4.

id.name: globosterol
id.definition: A 3beta-sterol that is 5alpha-androstane which contains a double bond between positions 7 and 8, in which the hydrogens at the 3beta, 5alpha and 6beta positions are substituted by hydroxy groups, and in which the hydrogen at the 17beta position is substituted by a (2S,3E,6xi)-6,7-dimethyloct-3-en-2-yl group. The polyhydroxylated C29 sterol was isolated from an endophytic fungus, Chaetomium globosum ZY-22; the stereochemistry at position 25 was not determined.

id.name: N(6)-(Delta(2)-isopentenyl)adenosine residue
id.definition: A nucleoside residue in which an adenosine residue has been modified by substitution at the 6-amino nitrogen by a Delta(2)-isopentenyl group.

id.name: adenosine residue
id.definition: The nucleoside residue formed from adenosine with linkages at the 3' and 5' positions.

id.name: 1-diphospho-1D-myo-inositol 2,3,4,5,6-pentakisphosphate
id.definition: A myo-inositol pentakisphosphate that consists of myo-inositol having the five phospho groups located at positions 2, 3, 4, 5 and 6 as well as a diphospho group at position 1.

id.name: icosatetraenoate
id.definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of icosatetraenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group. Major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: JH-02215
id.definition: A carboxylic ester-lactam that is a synthetic DDM (didehydroxymycobactin)-like lipopeptide.

id.name: alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-[alpha-D-GalpNAc-(1->3)]-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc
id.definition: A branched amino pentasaccharide consisting of the linear trisaccharide N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine having alpha-L-fucosyl residues attached at position 2 of the galactose and position 3 of the glucosamine. Corresponds to a partial structure of blood group A type 2 oligosaccharide.

id.name: sphingosine-1-phosphate receptor agonist
id.definition: An agonist that binds to and activates sphingosine 1-phosphate receptors.

id.name: dTDP-alpha-D-desosamine(1-)
id.definition: A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion that is the conjugate base of dTDP-alpha-D-desosamine, arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate group and protonation of the amino group.

id.name: UDP-2-acetamido-4-amino-2,4,6-trideoxy-alpha-D-glucose
id.definition: A UDP-amino sugar having 2-acetamido-4-amino-2,4,6-trideoxy-alpha-D-glucose as the sugar component.

id.name: dTDP-3-amino-3,6-dideoxy-alpha-D-galactopyranose(1-)
id.definition: A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups and protonation of the amino group of dTDP-3-amino-3,6-dideoxy-alpha-D-galactopyranose; major microspecies at pH 7.3.

id.name: glycodiaosylceramide
id.definition: An oligoglycosylceramide in which the oligoglycosyl component is derived from the cyclic form of a disaccharide (or derivative).

id.name: 8-azaguanine
id.definition: A triazolopyrimidine that consists of 3,6-dihydro-7H-[1,2,3]triazolo[4,5-d]pyrimidine bearing amino and oxo substituents at positions 5 and 7 respectively.

id.name: dTMP(2-)
id.definition: A 2'-deoxyribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of dTMP; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: lamivudine
id.definition: A monothioacetal that consists of cytosine having a (2R,5S)-2-(hydroxymethyl)-1,3-oxathiolan-5-yl moiety attached at position 1. An inhibitor of HIV-1 reverse transcriptase, it is used as an antiviral in the treatment of AIDS and hepatitis B.

id.name: iopromide
id.definition: A dicarboxylic acid diamide that consists of N-methylisophthalamide bearing three iodo substituents at positions 2, 4 and 6, a methoxyacetyl substituent at position 5 and two 2,3-dihydroxypropyl groups attached to the amide nitrogens. A water soluble x-ray contrast agent for intravascular administration.

id.name: 18-HETE
id.definition: A HETE that consists of arachidonic acid bearing a hydroxy substituent at position 18.

id.name: ribavirin
id.definition: A 1-ribosyltriazole that is the 1-ribofuranosyl derivative of 1,2,4-triazole-3-carboxamide. An inhibitor of HCV polymerase.

id.name: stavudine
id.definition: A nucleoside analogue obtained by formal dehydration across positions 2 and 3 of thymidine. An inhibitor of HIV-1 reverse transcriptase

id.name: leuprolide acetate
id.definition: An acetate salt obtained by combining the nonapeptide leuprolide with acetic acid. A long lasting GnRH analog, LH-Rh agonist. It is a synthetic nonapeptide analogue of gonadotropin-releasing hormone, and is used as a subcutaneous hydrogel implant for the treatment of prostate cancer and for the suppression of gonadal sex hormone production in children with central precocious puberty.

id.name: levofloxacin
id.definition: An optically active form of ofloxacin having (S)-configuration; an inhibitor of bacterial topoisomerase IV and DNA gyrase

id.name: fludarabine phosphate
id.definition: A purine arabinonucleoside monophosphate having 2-fluoroadenine as the nucleobase. A prodrug, it is rapidly dephosphorylated to 2-fluoro-ara-A and then phosphorylated intracellularly by deoxycytidine kinase to the active triphosphate, 2-fluoro-ara-ATP. Once incorporated into DNA, 2-fluoro-ara-ATP functions as a DNA chain terminator. It is used for the treatment of adult patients with B-cell chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL) who have not responded to, or whose disease has progressed during, treatment with at least one standard alkylating-agent containing regimenas.

id.name: linezolid
id.definition: An organofluorine compound that consists of 1,3-oxazolidin-2-one bearing an N-3-fluoro-4-(morpholin-4-yl)phenyl group as well as an acetamidomethyl group at position 5. A synthetic antibacterial agent that inhibits bacterial protein synthesis by binding to a site on 23S ribosomal RNA of the 50S subunit and prevents further formation of a functional 70S initiation complex.

id.name: mefloquine
id.definition: A racemate composed of (+)-(11R,2'S)- and (-)-(11S,2'R)-enantiomers of mefloquine. An antimalarial agent which acts as a blood schizonticide; its mechanism of action is unknown.

id.name: misoprostol
id.definition: A diastereoisomeric mixture composed of approximately equal amounts of a double racemate of four of the sixteen possible diastereoisomers of methyl (13E)-11,16-dihydroxy-16-methyl-9-oxoprost-13-en-1-oate that is racemic prostaglandin E1 which is lacking the hydroxy group at position 15, but which has an additional hydroxy group at position 16. It is a synthetic prostaglandin E1 analogue, used in the treatment of gastric and duodenal ulcers. A weak abortifacient, it is also used for cervical ripening prior to surgical termination of pregnancy. The (11R,16S)-diastereoisomer is the pharmacologically active form.

id.name: moxifloxacin
id.definition: A quinolone that consits of 4-oxo-1,4-dihydroquinoline-3-carboxylic acid bearing a cyclopropyl substituent at position 1, a fluoro substitiuent at position 6, a (4aS,7aS)-octahydro-6H-pyrrolo[3,4-b]pyridin-6-yl group at position 7 and a methoxy substituent at position 8. A member of the fluoroquinolone class of antibacterial agents.

id.name: nevirapine
id.definition: A dipyridodiazepine that is 5,11-dihydro-6H-dipyrido[3,2-b:2',3'-e][1,4]diazepine which is substituted by methyl, oxo, and cyclopropyl groups at positions 4, 6, and 11, respectively. A non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor with activity against HIV-1, it is used in combination with other antiretrovirals for the treatment of HIV infection.

id.name: olsalazine sodium
id.definition: An organic sodium salt that is the disodium salt of 3,3'-azobis(6-hydroxybenzoic acid) (olsalazine). Effective in the treatment of inflammatory bowel disease and ulcerative colitis. Mechanism of action unknown, but appears to be topical

id.name: pergolide
id.definition: A diamine that is ergoline in which the beta-hydrogen at position 8 is replaced by a (methylthio)methyl group and the hydrogen attached to the piperidine nitrogen (position 6) is replaced by a propyl group. A dopamine D2 receptor agonist which also has D1 and D2 agonist properties, it is used as the mesylate salt in the management of Parkinson's disease, although it was withdrawn from the U.S. and Canadian markets in 2007 due to an increased risk of cardiac valve dysfunction.

id.name: pravastatin
id.definition: A carboxylic ester resulting from the formal condensation of (S)-2-methylbutyric acid with the hydroxy group adjacent to the ring junction of (3R,5R)-7-[(1S,2S,6S,8S,8aR)-6,8-dihydroxy-2-methyl-1,2,6,7,8,8a-hexahydronaphthalen-1-yl]-3,5-dihydroxyheptanoic acid. Derived from microbial transformation of mevastatin, pravastatin is a reversible inhibitor of 3-hydroxy-3-methylglutaryl-coenzyme A (HMG-CoA). The sodium salt is used for lowering cholesterol and preventing cardiovascular disease. It is one of the lower potency statins, but has the advantage of fewer side effects compared with lovastatin and simvastatin.

id.name: propafenone
id.definition: An aromatic ketone that is 3-(propylamino)propane-1,2-diol in which the hydrogen of the primary hydroxy group is replaced by a 2-(3-phenylpropanoyl)phenyl group. It is a class 1C antiarrhythmic drug with local anesthetic effects, and is used as the hydrochloride salt in the management of supraventricular and ventricular arrhythmias.

id.name: saquinavir
id.definition: An aspartic acid derivative obtained by formal condensation of the primary amino group of (2S,3R)-4-[(3S,4aS,8aS)-3-(tert-butylcarbamoyl)octahydroisoquinolin-2(1H)-yl]-3-hydroxy-1-phenylbutan-2-ylamine with the carboxy group of N(2)(-quinolin-2-ylcarbonyl)-L-asparagine. An inhibitor of HIV-1 protease.

id.name: sotalol
id.definition: A sulfonamide that is N-phenylmethanesulfonamide in which the phenyl group is sustituted at position 4 by a 1-hydroxy-2-(isopropylamino)ethyl group. It has both beta-adrenoreceptor blocking (Vaughan Williams Class II) and cardiac action potential duration prolongation (Vaughan Williams Class III) antiarrhythmic properties. It is used (usually as the hydrochloride salt) for the management of ventricular and supraventricular arrhythmias.

id.name: succimer
id.definition: A sulfur-containing carboxylic acid that is succinic acid bearing two mercapto substituents at positions 2 and 3. A lead chelator used as an antedote to lead poisoning.

id.name: tinidazole
id.definition: 1H-imidazole substituted at C-1 by a (2-ethylsulfonyl)ethyl group, at C-2 by a methyl group and at C-5 by a nitro group. It is used as an antiprotozoal, antibacterial agent.

id.name: tizanidine
id.definition: 2,1,3-Benzothiadiazole substituted at C-4 by a Delta(1)-imidazolin-2-ylamino group and at C-4 by a chloro group. It is an agonist at alpha2-adrenergic receptor sites.

id.name: tolcapone
id.definition: Benzophenone substituted on one of the phenyl rings at C-3 and C-4 by hydroxy groups and at C-5 by a nitro group, and on the other phenyl ring by a methyl group at C-4. It is an inhibitor of catechol O-methyltransferase.

id.name: topiramate
id.definition: A hexose derivative that is 2,3:4,5-di-O-isopropylidene-beta-D-fructopyranose in which the hydroxy group has been converted to the corresponding sulfamate ester. It blocks voltage-dependent sodium channels and is used as an antiepileptic and for the prevention of migraine.

id.name: topotecan
id.definition: A pyranoindolizinoquinoline used as an antineoplastic agent. It is a derivative of camptothecin and works by binding to the topoisomerase I-DNA complex and preventing religation of these 328 single strand breaks.

id.name: valdecoxib
id.definition: A member of the class of isoxazoles that is isoxazole which is substituted at positions 3, 4 and 5 by phenyl, p-sulfamoylphenyl and methyl groups, respectively. A selective cyclooxygenase 2-inhibitor, it used as a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) for the treatment of arthritis from 2001 until 2005, when it was withdrawn following concerns of an associated increased risk of heart attack and stroke.

id.name: vigabatrin
id.definition: A gamma-amino acid having a gamma-vinyl GABA structure. It is an irreversible inhibitor of gamma-aminobutyric 664 acid transaminase

id.name: 26-hydroxycholest-4-en-3-one
id.definition: A cholestanoid that consists of 3-oxocholest-4-ene bearing a hydroxy substituent at position 26.

id.name: macrocyclic lactone
id.definition: Any lactone in which the cyclic carboxylic ester group forms a part of a cyclic macromolecule.

id.name: 11,12-DHET
id.definition: A DHET obtained by formal dihydroxylation across the 11,12-double bond of arachidonic acid.

id.name: 8,9-DHET
id.definition: A DHET obtained by formal dihydroxylation across the 8,9-double bond of arachidonic acid.

id.name: 5,6-DHET
id.definition: A DHET obtained by formal dihydroxylation across the 5,6-double bond of arachidonic acid.

id.name: (3Z)-2-oxohex-3-enedioate
id.definition: 2-Oxohex-3-enedioate in which the C=C double bond has Z configuration; principal microspecies at pH 7.3.

id.name: calcium nitrate
id.definition: Inorganic nitrate salt of calcium.

id.name: 8-bromo-3',5'-cyclic AMP
id.definition: A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide that is 3',5'-cyclic AMP bearing an additional bromo substituent at position 8 on the adenine ring. An activator of cyclic AMP-dependent protein kinase.

id.name: 2-phenoxyethanol
id.definition: An aromatic ether that is phenol substituted on oxygen by a 2-hydroxyethyl group.

id.name: glutaraldehyde
id.definition: A dialdehyde comprised of pentane with aldehyde functions at C-1 and C-5.

id.name: crizotinib
id.definition: A 3-[1-(2,6-dichloro-3-fluorophenyl)ethoxy]-5-[1-(piperidin-4-yl)pyrazol-4-yl]pyridin-2-amine that has R configuration at the chiral centre. The active enantiomer, it acts as a kinase inhibitor and is used for the treatment of patients with locally advanced or metastatic non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC)

id.name: memantine
id.definition: A primary aliphatic amine that is the 3,5-dimethyl derivative of 1-aminoadamantane. A low to moderate affinity uncompetitive (open-channel); NMDA receptor antagonist which binds preferentially to the NMDA receptor-operated cation channels.

id.name: metolazone
id.definition: A quinazoline that consists of 1,2,3,4-tetrahydroquinazolin-4-one bearing additional methyl, 2-tolyl, sulfamyl and chloro substituents at positions 2, 3, 6 and 7 respectively. A quinazoline diuretic, with properties similar to thiazide diuretics.

id.name: sumatriptan succinate
id.definition: A succinate salt obtained by reaction of sumatriptan with one equivalent of succinic acid. Selective agonist for a vascular 5-HT1 receptor subtype (probably a member of the 5-HT1D family). Used for the acute treatment of migraine with or without aura in adults.

id.name: O-(pantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue
id.definition: An anionic amino-acid residue formed by proton loss from the phospho group of an O-(pantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine residue, the principal form present at pH 7.3.

id.name: 1-heptadecene
id.definition: An unbranched seventeen-carbon alkene with one double bond between C-1 and C-2. It is produced by the Carrion beetles.

id.name: 1-[(7Z)-hexadecenoyl]-2-[(5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-eicosatetraenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 are 7Z-hexadecenoyl and 5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z-icosatetraenoyl respectively.

id.name: O-polysaccharide
id.definition: A repetitive glycan polysaccharide contained within a lipopolysaccharide (LPS). The O-antigen is attached to the core oligosaccharide, and comprises the outermost domain of the LPS molecule.

id.name: amyloid-beta
id.definition: A peptide of 36-43 amino acids that is processed from the amyloid precursor protein. Appears to be the main constituent of amyloid plaques (deposits found in the brains of Alzheimer's disease patients).

id.name: L-glutaminiumyl group
id.definition: The organic cationic group formed from L-glutaminium; the major structure at pH 7.3 of the L-glutaminyl group, formed by protonation of the alpha-amino group.

id.name: L-methioniniumyl group
id.definition: The organic cationic group formed from L-methioninium; the major structure at pH 7.3 of the L-methionyl group, formed by protonation of the alpha-amino group.

id.name: 2-monolysocardiolipin(2-)
id.definition: The organophosphate oxoanion formed from 2-monolysocardiolipin by deprotonation of the two phospho groups; principal species present at pH 7.3

id.name: EDTA disodium salt dihydrate
id.definition: A hydrate that is the dihydrate form of EDTA disodium salt.

id.name: 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol(1-)
id.definition: An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of any 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: [(1R)-2,2,3-trimethyl-5-oxocyclopent-3-enyl]acetyl-CoA(4-)
id.definition: The acyl-CoA oxoanion resulting from the removal of all four protons from the phosphate groups of [(1R)-2,2,3-trimethyl-5-oxocyclopent-3-enyl]acetyl-CoA. Major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: 1-palmitoyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate
id.definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are palmitoyl and oleoyl respectively.

id.name: 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol(1-)
id.definition: An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of any 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-D-myo-inositol; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: O-(pantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine residue
