id.definition: An alpha-amino-acid residue derived from O-(pantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine.

id.name: [(1R)-2,2,3-trimethyl-5-oxocyclopent-3-enyl]acetyl-CoA
id.definition: An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of [(1R)-2,2,3-trimethyl-5-oxocyclopent-3-en-1-yl]acetic acid.

id.name: inositol phosphoceramide(1-)
id.definition: An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the free phosphate OH group of any inositol phosphoceramide; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: ergosteryl palmitate
id.definition: A ergosteryl ester obtained by formal condensation of the 3-hydroxy group of ergosterol with the carboxy group of hexadecanoic (palmitic) acid. A natural product found in Chaetomium globosum and Chaetomium longirostre.

id.name: cichorine
id.definition: A member of the class of isoindoles that is 6-hydroxy-4-methoxy-5-methyl-2,3-dihydro-1H-isoindol-1-one which is substituted at position 4, 5, and 6 by methoxy, methyl, and hydroxy groups, respectively. A secondary metabolite found in Aspergillus silvativus, Aspergillus nidulans and Alternaria cichorii, it is poisonous to Russian knapweed (Acroptilon repens).

id.name: nicotine blue(2-)
id.definition: An organic anion obtained by selective deprotonation of the hydroxy groups at positions 2 and 2' of nicotine blue; major species at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).

id.name: 6,8-dimethyl-6,7-didehydroergolin-6-ium
id.definition: A cationic ergot alkaloid that is the 6,8-dimethyl-6,7-didehydro derivative of ergoline.

id.name: cyclo(tyrosyl-tyrosyl)
id.definition: A member of the class of 2,5-diketopiperazines that is piperazine-2,5-dione in which one hydrogen at position 3 and one hydrogen at position 6 are replaced by p-hydroxybenzyl groups.

id.name: 2-deoxystreptamine(2+)
id.definition: An organic cation obtained by protonation of the two free amino groups of 2-deoxystreptamine; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: (6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z)-3-oxotetracosahexaenoyl-CoA
id.definition: An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z)-3-oxotetracosahexaenoic acid. It is a member of n-3 PUFA and a product of alpha-linolenoic acid metabolism.

id.name: 1-alkyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol(1-)
id.definition: An alkyl,acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol(1-) in which unspecified alkyl and acyl groups are located at positions 1 and 2 respectively.

id.name: cytosin1-yl group
id.definition: An organic group obtained by removal of the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen at position 1 from cytosine.

id.name: N-tetradecanoylglycylpeptide(1-)
id.definition: A peptide anion formed by deprotonation of the terminal carboxy group of N-tetradecanoylglycylpeptide. Major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: 12-O-acetyl-16-O-deacetyl-16-epi-scalarobutenolide
id.definition: A scalarane sesterterpenoid isolated from the marine sponge Hyrtios erectus that exhibits antineoplastic activity.

id.name: ardisianoside E
id.definition: A triterpenoid saponin that is (3beta,16alphaalpha)-13,28-epoxyoleanane-3,16,30-triol with a beta-D-Glcp-(1->2)-[beta-D-Glcp-(1->4)]-alpha-L-Arap moiety attached to position 3 by a glycosidic linkage. It is isolated from Ardisia japonica and exhibits anticancer properties.

id.name: swertianolin
id.definition: A xanthone that is bellidifolin in which a beta-Dglucopyranosyl residue is attached at position O-8 via a glycosidic linkage. It is isolated particularly from Gentiana campestris and Gentiana germanica.

id.name: cochinchinone A
id.definition: A member of the class of xanthones that is 9H-xanthen-9-one substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 1, 3 and 7, a prenyl group at position 2 and a geranyl group at position 4. Isolated from Cratoxylum cochinchinense, it exhibits cytotoxic and antioxidant activities.

id.name: gedunin
id.definition: A pentacyclic triterpenoid natural product found particularly in Azadirachta indica and Cedrela odorata.

id.name: sch 213766
id.definition: A pyrrolidinone derivative that is the methyl ester of sch 210972. Isolated from fungal fermentation broth of Chaetomium globosum, it exhibits inhibitory activity against chemokine receptor CCR-5.

id.name: rediocide A
id.definition: A diterpenoid of the class of daphnane-type terpenes. It is isolated from Trigonostemon reidioides and has been shown to exhibit insecticidal activity.

id.name: rediocide C
id.definition: A diterpenoid of the class of daphnane-type terpenes. It is isolated from Trigonostemon thyrsoideum and has been shown to exhibit acaricidal activity.

id.name: (2S)-poncirin
id.definition: A flavanone glycoside that is 4'-methoxy-5,7-dihydroxyflavanone attached to a neohesperidose (alpha-L-rhamnopyranosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-glucopyranose) residue via a glycosidic linkage. It has been isolated from the fruits of Poncirus trifoliata and exhibits inhibitory activity against liopolysaccharide (LPS)-induced prostaglandin E2 and interleukin-6 (IL-6) production.

id.name: 4-nitrophenylhydrazine
id.definition: A member of the class of phenylhydrazines that is phenylhydrazine substituted at the 4-position by a nitro group.

id.name: 2,4-dinitrophenylhydrazine
id.definition: A C-nitro compound that is phenylhydrazine substituted at the 2- and 4-positions by nitro groups.

id.name: Delta(9)-tetrahydrocannabinol
id.definition: A diterpenoid that is 6a,7,8,10a-tetrahydro-6H-benzo[c]chromene substituted at position 1 by a hydroxy group, positions 6, 6 and 9 by methyl groups and at position 3 by a pentyl group. The principal psychoactive constituent of the cannabis plant, it is used for treatment of anorexia associated with AIDS as well as nausea and vomiting associated with cancer chemotherapy.

id.name: N-hexacosanoylicosasphinganine
id.definition: A C20 dihydroceramide in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as hexacosanoyl.

id.name: N-acylsphinganine-1-phosphocholine
id.definition: A sphingomyelin having sphinganine as the sphingoid component.

id.name: decyl beta-D-maltopyranoside
id.definition: A glycoside resulting from attachment of a decyl group to the reducing-end anomeric centre of a beta-maltose molecule.

id.name: phosphate monoester dianion
id.definition: Any organphosphate oxoanion resulting from the removal of both protons from the phosphate group of a phosphate monoester. The major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine
id.definition: A UDP-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine in which the anomeric centre of the galactosamine moiety has alpha-configuration.

id.name: 1-{4-[(2-hydroxyethyl)carbamoyl]benzyl}-1-methylpiperidinium
id.definition: Benzamide substituted on nitrogen by a 2-hydroxyethyl group and at the 4-position by an (N-methylpiperidinio)methyl group.

id.name: EC 3.2.1.20 (alpha-glucosidase) inhibitor
id.definition: An EC 3.2.1.* (glycosidase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of alpha-glucosidase (EC 3.2.1.20).

id.name: salannin
id.definition: A limonoid with insecticidal activity isolated from Azadirachta indica.

id.name: (+)-pisatin
id.definition: A member of the class of pterocarpans that is the 3-O-methyl ether of (+)-6a-hydroxymaackiain (the 6aR,12aR stereoisomer). A phytoalexin found in pods of garden peas (Pisum sativum) and other plants of the pea family, including Tephrosia candida.

id.name: clerodin
id.definition: A diterpenoid isolated from Ajuga bracteosa.

id.name: quercetin 3-O-beta-D-galactopyranoside
id.definition: A quercetin O-glycoside that is quercetin with a beta-D-galactosyl residue attached at position 3. Isolated from Artemisia capillaris, it exhibits hepatoprotective activity.

id.name: tamarixetin
id.definition: A monomethoxyflavone that is quercetin methylated at position O-4'. Isolated from Cyperus teneriffae.

id.name: chaetoviridin B
id.definition: An organic heterotetracyclic compound with formula C23H27ClO6 isolated from Chaetomium globosum. It exhibits antifungal activity against plant pathogenic fungi.

id.name: Effusanin B
id.definition: A natural product found in Isodon adenolomus.

id.name: Paravallarine
id.definition: A natural product found in Kibatalia laurifolia.

id.name: ginsenoside Rf
id.definition: A ginsenoside found in Panax ginseng and Panax japonicus var. major that is dammarane which is substituted by hydroxy groups at the 3beta, 6alpha, 12beta and 20 pro-S positions, in which the hydroxy group at position 6 has been converted to the corresponding beta-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-glucopyranoside, and in which a double bond has been introduced at the 24-25 position.

id.name: ginsenoside Rg1
id.definition: A ginsenoside found in Panax ginseng and Panax japonicus var. major that is dammarane which is substituted by hydroxy groups at the 3beta, 6alpha, 12beta and 20 pro-S positions, in which the hydroxy groups at positions 6 and 20 have been converted to the corresponding beta-D-glucopyranosides, and in which a double bond has been introduced at the 24-25 position.

id.name: syringic acid
id.definition: A dimethoxybenzene that is 3,5-dimethyl ether derivative of gallic acid.

id.name: phosphate group(2-)
id.definition: A doubly-charged inorganic anionic group arising from deprotonation of phosphate group.

id.name: EC 3.4.14.5 (dipeptidyl-peptidase IV) inhibitor
id.definition: An EC 3.4.14.* (dipeptidyl- and tripeptidyl-peptidases) inhibitor that specifically inhibits dipeptidyl peptidase-4 (EC 3.4.14.5).

id.name: 7,8-dihydroxy-1-methoxy-3-methyl-10-oxo-4,10-dihydro-1H,3H-pyrano[4,3-b]chromene-9-carboxylic acid
id.definition: An organic heterotricyclic compound that is 4,10-dihydro-1H,3H-pyrano[4,3-b]chromene substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 7 and 8, a methoxy group at position 1, a methyl group at position 3, an oxo group at position 10 and a carboxy group at position 9. Isolated from Chaetomium funicola it exhibits inhibitory activity against metallo-beta-lactamases.

id.name: chaetoviridin C
id.definition: An azaphilone that is 9,9a-dihydro-6H-furo[2,3-h]isochromene-6,8(6aH)-dione substituted by a chloro group at position 5, a 3-hydroxy-2-methylbutanoyl group at position 9, a methyl group at position 6a and a 3-methylpent-1-en-1yl group at position 3. It has been isolated from Chaetomium globosum.

id.name: chaetoviridin D
id.definition: An organic heterotetracyclic compound with formula C23H27ClO7 isolated from Chaetomium globosum. It is a diastereoisomer of chaetomugilin A (which has a significantly different optical rotation).

id.name: longirostrerone D
id.definition: An azaphilone that is 6H-furo[2,3-h]isochromene-6,8(6aH)-dione substituted by a 4-hydroxy-2-methyl-6-oxocyclohexyl group at position 3, a methyl group at position 6a, and a 4,6,8-trimethyldeca-2,4-dienoyl group at position 9. Isolated from Chaetomium longirostre, it exhibits cytotoxic activities.

id.name: bruceine D
id.definition: A quassinoid that is 13,20-epoxypicras-3-ene substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 1, 11, 12, 14 and 15 and oxo groups at positions 2 and 16. Isolated from the ethanol extract of the stem of Brucea mollis, it exhibits cytotoxic activity.

id.name: 13-oxo-9Z,11E-ODE
id.definition: An oxooctadecadienoic acid that consists of 9Z,11E-octadecadienoic acid bearing an additional 13-keto substituent. In addtion it has been found as a natural product found in Carthamus oxyacantha.

id.name: longirostrerone A
id.definition: An azaphilone that is 9,9a-dihydro-6H-furo[2,3-h]isochromene-6,8(6aH)-dione substituted by a 4-hydroxy-2-methyl-6-oxocyclohexyl group at position 3, a methyl group at position 6a and a 4,6,8-trimethyldeca-2,4-dienoyl group at position 9. Isolated from Chaetomium longirostre, it exhibits cytotoxic and antimalarial activities.

id.name: longirostrerone B
id.definition: An azaphilone that is 7,8-dihydro-6H-isochromen-6-one substituted by a hydroxy group at position 7, a 4-hydroxy-2-methyl-6-oxocyclohexyl group at position 3, a methyl group at position 7 and a 5,7,9-trimethyl-2-oxoundeca-3,5-dien-1-yl group at position 8. Isolated from Chaetomium longirostre, it exhibits cytotoxic and antimalarial activities.

id.name: longirostrerone C
id.definition: An azaphilone that is 9,9a-dihydro-6H-furo[2,3-h]isochromene-6,8(6aH)-dione substituted by a 6-methyl-2-oxocyclohex-3-en-1-yl group at position 3, a methyl group at position 6a and a 4,6,8-trimethyldeca-2,4-dienoyl group at position 9. Isolated from Chaetomium longirostre, it exhibits cytotoxic and antimalarial activities.

id.name: parfumine
id.definition: A benzylisoquinoline alkaloid isolated from Fumaria vaillantii and Fumaria parviflora.

id.name: Rutarin
id.definition: A natural product found in Citropsis articulata.

id.name: Seselin
id.definition: A natural product found in Citropsis articulata.

id.name: withaferin A
id.definition: A withanolide that is 5,6:22,26-diepoxyergosta-2,24-diene-1,26-dione substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 4 and 27 (the 4beta,5beta,6beta,22R stereoisomer). Isolated from Physalis longifolia, it exhibits cytotoxic activity.

id.name: latrunculin A
id.definition: A bicyclic macrolide natural product consisting of a 16-membered bicyclic lactone attached to the rare 2-thiazolidinone moiety. It is obtained from the Red Sea sponge Latrunculia magnifica and from the Fiji Islands sponge Cacospongia mycofijiensis. Latrunculin A inhibits actin polymerisation, microfilament organsation and microfilament-mediated processes.

id.name: aromaticin
id.definition: A sesquiterpene lactone that is 3,3a,4,4a,7a,8,9,9a-octahydroazuleno[6,5-b]furan-2,5-dione substituted by methyl groups at positions 4a and 8 and a methylidene group at position 3. Isolated from the aerial parts of Inula hupehensis, it exhibits anti-inflammatory activity.

id.name: stemofoline
id.definition: A natural product found in Stemona curtisii and Stemona aphylla.

id.name: carbonarone A
id.definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide that is 4H-pyran-3-carboxamide substituted by an oxo group at position 4 and a benzyl group at position 6. It has been isolated from Aspergillus niger and Aspergillus carbonarius.

id.name: pestalamide A
id.definition: A pyranone that is (2S)-2-methyl-4-oxo-4-{[(4-oxo-4H-pyran-3-yl)carbonyl]amino}butanoic acid substituted by a benzyl group at position 6. It has been isolated from Aspergillus niger.

id.name: ergosta-4,6,8(14),22-tetraen-3-one
id.definition: An ergostanoid that is (22E)-ergosta-4,6,8(14),22-tetraene substituted by an oxo group at position 3. It has been isolated from the mycelia of Cordyceps sinensis.

id.name: orobol
id.definition: A member of the class of 7-hydroxyisoflavones which consists of isoflavone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 5, 7, 3' and 4'. It has been isolated from the mycelia of Cordyceps sinensis.

id.name: cannabidiol
id.definition: An cannabinoid that is cyclohexene which is substituted by a methyl group at position 1, a 2,6-dihydroxy-4-pentylphenyl group at position 3, and a prop-1-en-2-yl group at position 4.

id.name: Bergenin
id.definition: A natural product found in Cenostigma gardnerianum.

id.name: rubiadin
id.definition: A dihydroxyanthraquinone that is anthracene-9,10-dione substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 1 and 3 and a methyl group at position 2. It has been isolated from Rubia yunnanensis.

id.name: Paeonol
id.definition: A natural product found in Paeonia rockii subspeciesrockii.

id.name: Trichothecin
id.definition: A natural product found in Trichothecium speciesMSX 51320.

id.name: oxypeucedanin
id.definition: A furanocoumarin that is 7H-furo[3,2-g][1]benzopyran-7-one substituted by a [(2S)-3,3-dimethyloxiran-2-yl]methoxy group at position 4.

id.name: Ostruthin
id.definition: A natural product found in Peucedanum ostruthium.

id.name: Murrayanine
id.definition: A natural product found in Clausena harmandiana.

id.name: Mammea E/BB
id.definition: A natural product found in Mammea americana.

id.name: pachypodol
id.definition: A trimethoxyflavone that is quercetin in which the hydroxy groups at position 3, 7 and 3' are replaced by methoxy groups. It has been isolated from Combretum quadrangulare and Euodia elleryana.

id.name: 2'-hydroxygenistein
id.definition: A hydroxyisoflavone that is genistein substituted by an additional hydroxy group at position 2'. It has been isolated from Crotalaria lachnophora.

id.name: cajanol
id.definition: A hydroxyisoflavanone that is (3S)-isoflavanone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 5 and 4' and methoxy groups at positions 7 and 2' respectively. It has been isolated from Crotalaria lachnophora.

id.name: Cajanin
id.definition: A natural product found in Crotalaria lachnophora.

id.name: myricitrin
id.definition: A glycosyloxyflavone that consists of myricetin attached to a alpha-L-rhamnopyranosyl residue at position 3 via a glycosidic linkage. Isolated from Myrica cerifera, it exhibits anti-allergic activity.

id.name: Monocerin
id.definition: A natural product found in Colletotrichum species.

id.name: Narciclasine
id.definition: A natural product found in Narcissus pseudonarcissus.

id.name: militarinone B
id.definition: A natural product found in Isaria farinosa.

id.name: phenazine-1,6-dicarboxylic acid
id.definition: A member of the class of phenazines carrying carboxy substituents at positions 1 and 6. A natural product found in Streptomyces species.

id.name: Candimine
id.definition: A natural product found in Hippeastrum morelianum and Hippeastrum candidum.

id.name: Apiole
id.definition: A natural product found in Petroselinum sativum.

id.name: Enmein
id.definition: A natural product found in Isodon eriocalyx.

id.name: Dillapiole
id.definition: A natural product found in Anethum graveolens.

id.name: liriodenine
id.definition: An oxoaporphine alkaloid that is 4,5,6,6a-tetradehydronoraporphin-7-one substituted by a methylenedioxy group across positions 1 and 2. It is isolated from Annona glabra and has been shown to exhibit antimicrobial and cytotoxic activities.

id.name: thiophene-2-carboxylic acid
id.definition: A thiophenecarboxylic acid in which the carboxy group is located at position 2.

id.name: nitrofurantoin
id.definition: An imidazolidine-2,4-dione that is hydantoin substituted at position 1 by a [(5-nitro-2-furyl)methylene]amino group. An antibiotic that damages bacterial DNA.

id.name: phenazopyridine
id.definition: A diaminopyridine that is 2,6-diaminopyridine substituted at position 3 by a phenylazo group. A local anesthetic that has topical analgesic effect on mucosa lining of the urinary tract. Its use is limited by problems with toxicity (primarily blood disorders) and potential carcinogenicity.

id.name: procarbazine
id.definition: A benzamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 4-[(2-methylhydrazino)methyl]benzoic acid with the amino group of isopropylamine. An antineoplastic chemotherapy drug used for treatment of Hodgkin's lymphoma. Metabolism yields azo-procarbazine and hydrogen peroxide, which results in the breaking of DNA strands.

id.name: triamcinolone acetonide
id.definition: A synthetic glucocorticoid that is the 16,17-acetonide of triamcinolone. Used to treat various skin infections.

id.name: procarbazine hydrochloride
id.definition: A hydrochloride obtained by combining procarbazine with one equivalent of hydrochloric acid. An antineoplastic chemotherapy drug used for treatment of Hodgkin's lymphoma. Metabolism yields azo-procarbazine and hydrogen peroxide, which results in the breaking of DNA strands.

id.name: oleoyl ethanolamide
id.definition: An N-(long-chain-acyl)ethanolamine that is the ethanolamide of oleic acid. The monounsaturated analogue of the endocannabinoid anandamide

id.name: beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1-1')-Cer(1-)
id.definition: An N-acetylneuraminate that is the conjugate base of beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc-(1-1')-Cer, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc
id.definition: An amino disaccharide comprising a beta-D-mannose residue linked (1->4) to an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue at the reducing end.

id.name: (2S)-2-hydroxy-3,4-diketopentyl phosphate
id.definition: A monoalkyl phosphate that is pentane substituted at positions 3 and 4 by oxo groups, at position 2 by a hydroxy group and at position 1 by a phosphooxy group (the S-enantiomer).

id.name: tadalafil
id.definition: A pyrazinopyridoindole that is 2,3,6,7,12,12a-hexahydropyrazino[1',2':1,6]pyrido[3,4-b]indole-1,4-dione substituted at position 2 by a methyl group and at position 6 by a 1,3-benzodioxol-5-yl group (the 6R,12aR-diastereomer). A phosphodiesterase V inhibitor inhibitor, currently marketed in pill form for treating erectile dysfunction under the name Cialis; and under the name Adcirca for the treatment of pulmonary arterial hypertension.

id.name: tolmetin
id.definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is (1-methylpyrrol-2-yl)acetic acid substituted at position 5 on the pyrrole ring by a 4-methylbenzoyl group. Used in the form of its sodium salt dihydrate as a nonselective nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug.

id.name: proansamycin X
id.definition: A 26-membered macrocylic polyketide incorporating a quinone ring as well as lactam and enone functionality. An intermediate in the biosynthesis of rifamycin.

id.name: hydroxyflavan
id.definition: A member of the class of flavans in which one or more ring hydrogens are replaced by hydroxy groups.

id.name: pyrithiamine
id.definition: A pyridinium ion that is 3-(2-hydroxyethyl)-2-methylpyridine substituted at position 1 by a (4-amino-2-methylpyrimidin-5-yl)methyl group.

id.name: WR-1065
id.definition: An alkanethiol that is the N-3-aminopropyl derivative of cysteamine. Used as the S-phosphorylated prodrug, amifostine, for cytoprotection in cancer chemotherapy and radiotherapy.

id.name: O-oleoylcarnitine
id.definition: An O-acylcarnitine having oleoyl as the acyl substituent.

id.name: (2R)-trihomocitric acid
id.definition: A chiral tricarboxylic acid in which a central carbon carries hydroxy, carboxy, carboxymethyl and 4-carboxybutyl substituents with R-configuration at the chiral centre.

id.name: 13-oxo-9E,11E-ODE
id.definition: An oxooctadecadienoic acid that consists of 9E,11E-octadecadienoic acid with the oxo substituent located at position 13.

id.name: 1,2-dipalmitoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-)
id.definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-) in which both acyl groups are specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl); major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: icosadienoic acid
id.definition: A 20-carbon, polyunsaturated fatty acid having two double bonds at unspecified positions.

id.name: 1-hexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A lysophosphatidylcholine 16:0 in which a hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) group is attached to the glycero moiety at position 1.

id.name: 1,2-dihexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A phosphatidylcholine 32:0 in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl). A synthetic phospholipid used in liposomes and lipid bilayers to study biological membranes. It is also a major constituent of pulmonary surfactants.

id.name: 1-hexadecanoyl-2-(9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A phosphatidylcholine 34:2 in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) and 9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl (linoleoyl) respectively.

id.name: 1-palmitoyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A phosphatidylcholine 36:4 in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) and 5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z-eicosatetraenoyl (arachidonoyl) respectively.

id.name: 1-hexadecanoyl-2-(9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion
id.definition: A phosphatidylethanolamine 34:2 zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the phosphate to the amino group of 1-hexadecanoyl-2-(9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine.

id.name: 3-hydroxyisovalerylcarnitine
id.definition: An O-acylcarnitine having 3-hydroxyisovaleryl as the acyl substituent.

id.name: O-methylmalonylcarnitine
id.definition: An O-acylcarnitine having methylmalonyl as the acyl substituent.

id.name: victorin C
id.definition: A heterodetic cyclic peptide produced by the fungus Cochliobolus victoriae that is required for pathogenicity in the organism

id.name: 2,4-DB
id.definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is butyric acid in which one of the hydrogens at position 4 is replaced by a 2,4-dichlorophenoxy group. A selective post-emergence herbicide.

id.name: 2,3,5-triiodobenzoic acid
id.definition: A member of the class of benzoic acids that is benzoic acid in which the hydrogens at positions 2, 3 and 5 are replaced by iodine atoms. It is an auxin polar transport inhibitor.

id.name: EC 3.6.* (hydrolases acting on acid anhydrides) inhibitor
id.definition: Any hydrolase inhibitor that interferes with the action of a hydrolase which acts on acid anhydrides (EC 3.6.*.*).

id.name: (-)-noscapine
id.definition: A benzylisoquinoline alkaloid that is 1,2,3,4-tetrahydroisoquinoline which is substituted by a 4,5-dimethoxy-3-oxo-1,3-dihydro-2-benzofuran-1-yl group at position 1, a methylenedioxy group at positions 6-7 and a methoxy group at position 8. Obtained from plants of the Papaveraceae family, it lacks significant painkilling properties and is primarily used for its antitussive (cough-suppressing) effects.

id.name: N-hexacosanoylisoglobotriaosyl ceramide
id.definition: The N-hexacosanoyl derivative of isoglobotriaosyl ceramide.

id.name: sodium 2-amino-5-[(1-methoxy-2-methylindolizin-3-yl)carbonyl]benzoate
id.definition: An organic sodium salt having 2-amino-5-[(1-methoxy-2-methylindolizin-3-yl)carbonyl]benzoate as the counterion.

id.name: N-ethyl-5'-carboxamidoadenosine
id.definition: A derivative of adenosine in which the 5'-hydroxymethyl group is replaced by an N-ethylcarboxamido group.

id.name: 1-alkylglycerone 3-phosphate(2-)
id.definition: An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of any 1-alkylglycerone 3-phosphate.

id.name: alpha-CH2-containing aldehyde
id.definition: An aldehyde of general formula R-CH2-CH=O in which the aldehydic C=O function is attached to a CH2 group at the alpha-position.

id.name: promegestone
id.definition: A progestin consisting of 17beta-propionylestra-4,9-dien-3-one substituted at position 17 by a methyl group.

id.name: acetylide
id.definition: A compound arising by replacement of one or both hydrogen atoms of acetylene (ethyne) by a metal or other cationic group. By extension, the class of acetylides includes analogous compounds derived from terminal acetylenic compound, RC#CH.

id.name: asukamycin
id.definition: A polyketide that is a member of the manumycin family of antibiotics and exhibits strong antibacterial, antifungal, and antineoplastic activities. Isolated from from the actinomycete bacterium Streptomyces nodosus subsp. asukaensis.

id.name: gamma-Glu-Gln
id.definition: A dipeptide obtained by formal condensation of the gamma-carboxy group of glutamic acid with the amino group of glutamine

id.name: PPARbeta/delta agonist
id.definition: A PPAR modulator which activates the peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor-beta/delta.

id.name: 1-arachidonoyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate
id.definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate in which the 1-O-acyl group is specified as arachidonoyl.

id.name: 1-tetradecanoyl-2-(11Z-octadecenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A phosphatidylcholine 32:1 in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 are tetradecanoyl and (11Z)-octadec-11-enoyl respectively.

id.name: 1-stearoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A lysophosphatidylcholine 18:0 in which the acyl substituent is located at position 1 and is specified as stearoyl.

id.name: cholesteryl (7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosapentaenoate
id.definition: A cholesterol ester with the acyl group as (7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosa-7,10,13,16,19-pentaenyl.

id.name: 2-oleoylglycerol
id.definition: A 2-monoglyceride where the acyl group is (9Z)-octadecenoyl.

id.name: 1-hexadecanoyl-2-[(9Z)-hexadec-9-enoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion
id.definition: A phosphatidylethanolamine 32:1 in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 are hexadecanoyl and (9Z)-hexadec-9-enoyl respectively.

id.name: 1-palmitoyl-2-palmitoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A phosphatidylcholine 32:1 in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 are hexadecanoyl and (9Z)-hexadec-9-enoyl respectively.

id.name: 16-carboxy-17,18,19,20-tetranor-leukotriene E3
id.definition: An icosanoid that is leukotriene E4 in which the non-conjugated double bond has been reduced to a single bond and four methylene groups have been lost from the resulting carboxyalkyl chain.

id.name: dioscin
id.definition: A spirostanyl glycoside that consists of the trisaccharide alpha-L-Rha-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Rha-(1->2)]-beta-D-Glc attached to position 3 of diosgenin via a glycosidic linkage.

id.name: 3-amino-4,7-dihydroxy-8-methylcoumarin
id.definition: A hydroxycoumarin that is 4,7-dihydroxycoumarin bearing additional amino and methyl substituents at positions 3 and 8 respectively.

id.name: aclacinomycin T
id.definition: An anthracycline that is aklavinone having an alpha-L-rhodosaminyl residue attached at position 4 via a glycosidic linkage.

id.name: N(6)-L-threonylcarbamoyladenine 5'-monophosphate(2-) residue
id.definition: An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the free phosphate OH and carboxy groups of N(6)-L-threonylcarbamoyladenine 5'-monophosphate residue.

id.name: 1-octadecanoyl-2-(7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatetraenoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
id.definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as octadecanoyl and (7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatetraenoyl respectively.

id.name: 1,2-dioleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-)
id.definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1,2-dioleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate.

id.name: 5,6-dihydrouridine 5'-monophosphate
id.definition: A uridine 5'-phosphate that is the 5,6-dihydro derivative of uridine 5'-monophosphate.

id.name: N(2)-methylguanosine 5'-monophosphate
id.definition: A purine ribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate that is GMP bearing an N(2)-methyl substituent.

id.name: Pro-Hyp
id.definition: A dipeptide composed of L-proline and L-hydroxyproline residues. It is a biomarker for bone collagen degradation.

id.name: 2-methyladenosine 5'-monophosphate
id.definition: A purine ribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate having 2-methyladenine as the nucleobase.

id.name: N(3)-methyluridine 5'-monophosphate
id.definition: A pyrimidine ribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate having 3-methyluracil as the nucleobase.

id.name: 3'-O-methylcyanidin 3-O-beta-D-glucoside
id.definition: An anthocyanin cation that is the 3-O-beta-D-glucoside of methylcyanidin (peonidin).

id.name: apiforol
id.definition: A tetrahydroxyflavan in which the four hydroxy substituents are located at positions 4, 4', 5 and 7.

id.name: 1-stearoyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate
id.definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate in which the acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as stearoyl and oleoyl respectively.

id.name: pentan-1-amine
id.definition: A primary aliphatic amine that is n-pentane in which a hydrogen of one of the methyl groups is replaced by an amino group. A water-soluble liquid with boiling point 104degreeC, it is a strong irritant.

id.name: isocaproic acid
id.definition: A methyl-branched fatty acid that is pentanoic acid with a methyl group substituent at position 4. It is a metabolite of 20 alpha-hydroxycholesterol

id.name: 1-acyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-)
id.definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of any 1-acyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate.

id.name: 4',6,7-trihydroxyisoflavone
id.definition: A hydroxyisoflavone that is daidzein bearing an additional hydroxy substituent at position 6.

id.name: homoeriodictyol
id.definition: A trihydroxyflavanone that consists of 3'-methoxyflavanone in which the three hydroxy substituents are located at positions 4', 5, and 7.

id.name: 1-hexadecanoyl-2-(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z-docosahexaenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A phosphatidylcholine 38:6 in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 are specified as hexadecanoyl and (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl respectively.

id.name: rhamnetin
id.definition: A monomethoxyflavone that is quercetin methylated at position 7.

id.name: malvin
id.definition: An anthocyanin cation that is malvidin carrying two beta-D-glucosyl residues at positions 3 and 5.

id.name: peonidin chloride
id.definition: An anthocyanidin chloride that has peonidin as the cationic component.

id.name: 1-stearoyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A phosphatidylcholine 36:1 in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are stearoyl and oleoyl respectively.

id.name: petunidin chloride
id.definition: An anthocyanidin chloride that has petunidin as the cationic component.

id.name: 1-acyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero 3-phosphocholine in which the acyl group at position 1 is unspecified while that at position 2 is specified as arachidonoyl

id.name: 1-acyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion
id.definition: 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl group at position 1 is unspecified while that at position 2 is specified as arachidonoyl

id.name: N(4)-acetylcytidine 5'-monophosphate
id.definition: A pyrimidine ribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate having N(4)-acetylcytosine as the nucleobase.

id.name: morin
id.definition: A pentahydroxyflavone that is 7-hydroxyflavonol bearing three additional hydroxy substituents at positions 2' 4' and 5.

id.name: chrysin
id.definition: A dihydroxyflavone in which the two hydroxy groups are located at positions 5 and 7.

id.name: datiscetin
id.definition: A tetrahydroxyflavone that is 7-hydroxyflavonol bearing two additional hydroxy substituents at positions 2' and 5.

id.name: 2,2'-dilysocardiolipin(2-)
id.definition: An anionic phospholipid obtained by deprotonation of both free phosphate OH groups of any 2,2'-dilysocardiolipin.

id.name: N-benzyloxycarbonyl-L-leucyl-L-leucyl-L-leucinal
id.definition: A tripeptide that is L-leucyl-L-leucyl-L-leucine in which the C-terminal carboxy group has been reduced to the corresponding aldehyde and the N-terminal amino group is protected as its benzyloxycarbonyl derivative.

id.name: 1-myristoyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphatidylglycerol(1-)
id.definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-) in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as myristoyl and oleoyl respectively; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: 1,2-dioleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-)
id.definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-) in which both acyl groups are specified as oleoyl.

id.name: patuletin
id.definition: A trimethoxyflavone that is quercetagetin methylated at position 6.

id.name: 1-acyl-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-)
id.definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-) in which the acyl group at position 1 is unspecified while that at position 2 is specified as oleoyl

id.name: 3',5'-cyclic UMP
id.definition: A 3',5'-cyclic pyrimidine nucleotide having uridine as the nucleobase.

id.name: trifluridine
id.definition: A pyrimidine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside compound having 5-trifluoromethyluracil as the nucleobase. An antiviral drug used mainly in the treatment of primary keratoconjunctivitis and recurrent epithelial keratitis.

id.name: alpha-D-mannosyl group
id.definition: A mannosyl group derived from alpha-D-mannose.

id.name: 1-O-octadecyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A 1-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alkyl group is specified as octadecyl

id.name: 1-acyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1D-myo-inositol(1-)
id.definition: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol(1-) in which the phosphatidyl acyl group at position 2 is specified as arachidonoyl while that at position 2 remains unspecified.

id.name: aklaviketone
id.definition: A carboxylic ester that is the methyl ester of (1R,2R)-2-ethyl-2,5,7-trihydroxy-4,6,11-trioxo-1,2,3,4,6,11-hexahydrotetracene-1-carboxylic acid.

id.name: 1-O-octadecyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A phosphatidylcholine O-38:4 in which the alkyl and acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are octadecyl and (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-eicosatetraenoyl respectively.

id.name: picropodophyllotoxin
id.definition: An organic heterotetracyclic compound that has a furonaphthodioxole skeleton bearing 3,4,5-trimethoxyphenyl and hydroxy substituents.

id.name: arotinoid acid
id.definition: A retinoid that consists of benzoic acid substituted at position 4 by a 2-(5,5,8,8-tetramethyl-5,6,7,8-tetrahydronaphthalen-2-yl)prop-1-en-1-yl group. It is a synthetic retinoid that acts as a selective agonist for the retinoic acid receptors (RAR).

id.name: epsilon-rhodomycinone
id.definition: A carboxylic ester that is the methyl ester of (1R,2R,4S)-2-ethyl-2,4,5,7,12-pentahydroxy-6,11-dioxo-1,2,3,4,6,11-hexahydrotetracene-1-carboxylic acid.

id.name: 1-icosanoyl-2-palmitoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A phosphatidylcholine 36:0 where the acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are icosanoyl and palmitoyl respectively.

id.name: glutamine hydroxamate
id.definition: A hydroxamic acid that is L-glutamine hydroxylated at N-5.

id.name: 19-oxotestosterone
id.definition: An androstanoid that is testosterone with an oxo group at position 19.

id.name: methyl aklanonate
id.definition: A methyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of aklanonic acid with methanol.

id.name: 1-palmitoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)
id.definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol) in which the 1-acyl substituent is specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl).

id.name: 2-tetradecanoylglycerol
id.definition: A 2-monoglyceride where the acyl group is tetradecanoyl (myristoyl).

id.name: 1-octadecanoyl-2-[(9Z)-octadecenoyl]-sn-glycerol
id.definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol that has stearoyl and oleoyl as the 1- and 2-acyl groups respectively.

id.name: 4-O-sinapoylquinic acid
id.definition: A cinnamate ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of sinapic acid with the 4-hydroxy group of (-)-quinic acid.

id.name: 1-lauroyl-sn-glycerol
id.definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycerol that is the S-enantiomer of 2,3-dihydroxypropyl dodecanoate (glyceryl monolaurate).

id.name: 1-hexadecanoyl-sn-glycerol
id.definition: A 1-acyl-sn-glycerol that has hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) as the 1-acyl group.

id.name: rac-1-monolauroylglycerol
id.definition: A rac-1-monoacylglycerol comprising equal amounts of 1-lauroyl-sn-glycerol and 3-lauroyl-sn-glycerol

id.name: rac-1-monodecanoylglycerol
id.definition: A rac-1-monoacylglycerol composed of equal amounts of 3-decanoyl-sn-glycerol and 1-decanoyl-sn-glycerol.

id.name: 1-monostearoylglycerol
id.definition: A 1-monoglyceride that has stearoyl as the acyl group.

id.name: rac-1-monomyristoylglycerol
id.definition: A rac-1-monoacylglycerol that is composed of equal amounts of 1-myristoyl-sn-glycerol and 3-myristoyl-sn-glycerol.

id.name: 3-arachidonoyl-sn-glycerol
id.definition: A 3-acyl-sn-glycerol where arachidonoyl is the 3-acyl group.

id.name: 1,2-hexadecanediol
id.definition: A glycol that is hexadecane which is substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 1 and 2.

id.name: O-acyl-L-carnitine
id.definition: An O-acylcarnitine in which the carnitine component has L-configuration.

id.name: sarin
id.definition: A racemate composed of equal amounts of (R)- and (S)-sarin. A potent and irreversible inhibitor of acetylcholinesterase that is toxic to the nervous system and is employed as a chemical warfare agent.

id.name: genkwanin
id.definition: A monomethoxyflavone that is apigenin in which the hydroxy group at position 7 is methylated.

id.name: animal metabolite
id.definition: Any eukaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in animals that include diverse creatures from sponges, insects to mammals.

id.name: mammalian metabolite
id.definition: Any animal metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in mammals.

id.name: Saccharomyces cerevisiae metabolite
id.definition: Any fungal metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in Baker's yeast (Saccharomyces cerevisiae).

id.name: (7R)-hydroxy-(5S,6S)-epoxy-(8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoic acid
id.definition: A trienoic fatty acid consisting of (8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosa-8,11,14-trienoic acid having additional (7R)-hydroxy- and (5S,6S)-epoxy groups.

id.name: iron(2+) sulfate heptahydrate
id.definition: A hydrate that is the heptahydrate form of iron(2+) sulfate. It is used as a source of iron in the treatment of iron-deficiency anaemia (generally in liquid-dosage treatments; for solid-dosage treatments, the monohydrate is normally used).

id.name: hispidulin
id.definition: A monomethoxyflavone that is scutellarein methylated at position 6.

id.name: 1-(beta-D-galactosyl)-N-behenoylsphingosine
id.definition: A D-galactosyl-N-acylsphingosine where the ceramide N-acyl group is docosananoyl and the D-galactosyl component has beta anomeric configuration.

id.name: flecainide
id.definition: A monocarboxylic acid amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2,5-bis(2,2,2-trifluoroethoxy)benzoic acid with the primary amino group of piperidin-2-ylmethylamine. An antiarrhythmic agent used (in the form of its acetate salt) to prevent and treat tachyarrhythmia (abnormal fast rhythm of the heart).

id.name: teniposide
id.definition: A furonaphthodioxole that is a synthetic derivative of podophyllotoxin with anti-tumour activity; causes single- and double-stranded breaks in DNA and DNA-protein cross-links and prevents repair by topoisomerase II binding.

id.name: thioflavine T
id.definition: An organic chloride salt having 2-[4-(dimethylamino)phenyl]-3,6-dimethyl-1,3-benzothiazol-3-ium as the counterion. It is widely used to visualise and quantify the presence of amyloids, both in vitro and in vivo.

id.name: dTDP-beta-L-4-epi-vancosamine
id.definition: A dTDP-sugar having beta-L-4-epi-vancosamine as the sugar component.

id.name: nicotinic acid-adenine dinucleotide phosphate
id.definition: A nicotinic acid dinucleotide that is NADP(+) in which the carboxamide group on the pyridine ring is replaced by a carboxy group.

id.name: 2-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A lysophosphatidylcholine 18:2 in which the acyl group is specified as linoleoyl and is located at position 2.

id.name: sodium sulfide (anhydrous)
id.definition: A sulfide salt with formula Na2S. The pentahydrate and (particularly) the nonahydrate are also known. In gel form, sodium sulfide is used to soften toenails to assist in trimming (and so relive pain) of ingrowing toenails.

id.name: 1-alkyl-3-acylglycerol
id.definition: A monoglyceride in which the acyl group is located at position 3 with an additional alkyl substituent at position 1.

id.name: marine metabolite
id.definition: Any metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in marine macro- and microorganisms.

id.name: beta-D-glucosyl-(1->3)-alpha-L-fucosyl group
id.definition: A fucosyl group in which D-Glc is linked beta(1->3) to an L-fucosyl group which has alpha-configuration at its anomeric centre.

id.name: alk-1-enylacylglycerol
id.definition: A disubstituted glycerol that consists of glycerol carrying one acyl and one alk-1-enyl substituent at unspecified positions.

id.name: EC 2.7.10.2 (non-specific protein-tyrosine kinase) inhibitor
id.definition: An EC 2.7.10.* (protein-tyrosine kinase) inhibitor that specifically blocks the action of non-specific protein-tyrosine kinase (EC 2.7.10.2).

id.name: S-methyl-L-ergothioneine
id.definition: An amino acid betaine that is ergothioneine in which the hydrogen attached to the sulfur is replaced by a methyl group. It has been isolated from the deepwater (500-1,600 m) marine sponge Macandrewia azorica.

id.name: 2-hydroxyoctadecanoate
id.definition: A 2-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 2-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid (stearic acid), obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: plant metabolite
id.definition: Any eukaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in plants, the kingdom that include flowering plants, conifers and other gymnosperms.

id.name: fungal metabolite
id.definition: Any eukaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in fungi, the kingdom that includes microorganisms such as the yeasts and moulds.

id.name: Aspergillus metabolite
id.definition: Any fungal metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in the mould, Aspergillus.

id.name: Chaetomium metabolite
id.definition: Any fungal metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in the mould, Chaetomium.

id.name: Penicillium metabolite
id.definition: Any fungal metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in Penicillium.

id.name: bacterial metabolite
id.definition: Any prokaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in bacteria.

id.name: Streptococcus pneumoniae metabolite
id.definition: Any bacterial metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in Streptococcus pneumoniae.

id.name: trioctanoin
id.definition: A triglyceride obtained by acylation of the three hydroxy groups of glycerol by octanoic acid. Used as an alternative energy source to glucose for patients with mild to moderate Alzheimer's disease.

id.name: N,N-dimethyl-L-alanine
id.definition: A methyl-L-alanine in which both the amino hydrogens of L-alanine are replaced by methyl groups.

id.name: 6-sulfoquinovose(1-)
id.definition: An organosulfonate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of 6-sulfoquinovose, obtained by deprotonation of the sulfonate OH group; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: ginsenoside Re
id.definition: A ginsenoside found in Panax ginseng that is dammarane which is substituted by hydroxy groups at the 3beta, 6alpha, 12beta and 20 pro-S positions, in which the hydroxy groups at positions 6 and 20 have been converted to the corresponding alpha-L-rhamnopyranosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-glucopyranoside and beta-D-glucopyranoside respectively, and in which a double bond has been introduced at the 24-25 position.

id.name: notoginsenoside R1
id.definition: A ginsenoside found in Panax notoginseng that is dammarane which is substituted by hydroxy groups at the 3beta, 6alpha, 12beta and 20 pro-S positions, in which the hydroxy groups at positions 6 and 20 have been converted to the corresponding beta-D-xylopyranosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-glucopyranoside and beta-D-glucopyranoside respectively, and in which a double bond has been introduced at the 24-25 position.

id.name: alpha-NADH(2-)
id.definition: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the two diphosphate OH groups of alpha-NADH; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: 1-(Z)-alk-1-enyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion
id.definition: A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the alkenyl group has Z geochemistry.

id.name: 1-(1Z)-hexadecenyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A 1-O-(alk-1-enyl)-2-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alk-1-enyl and acyl groups are specified as (1Z)-hexadecenyl and arachidonoyl respectively.

id.name: 1,8-dihydroxy-4-nitroxanthen-9-one
id.definition: A member of the class of xanthones that is xanthen-9-one substituted at position 4 by a nitro group and at positions 1 and 8 by hydroxy groups.

id.name: dotriacontan-1-ol
id.definition: A long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is dotriacontane in which a hydrogen attached to one of the terminal carbons is replaced by a hydroxy group.

id.name: 4-amino-2,6-dinitrotoluene
id.definition: An amino-nitrotoluene that is 2,6-dinitrotoluene substituted at position 4 by an amino group.

id.name: (4R)-4-hydroxy-L-lysine
id.definition: A 4-hydrox-L-lysine that is L-lysine substituted at position 4 by a hydroxy group (the 4R-threo-stereoisomer).

id.name: 1-pentadecene
id.definition: An unbranched fifteen-carbon alkene with one double bond between C-1 and C-2.

id.name: 3-ethyltoluene
id.definition: A derivative of toluene bearing an additional ethyl substituent at position 3.

id.name: human metabolite
id.definition: Any mammalian metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in humans (Homo sapiens).

id.name: (7R)-hydroxy-(5S,6S)-epoxy-(8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoate
id.definition: A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (7R)-hydroxy-(5S,6S)-epoxy-(8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: 4-coumaroyltriacetic acid lactone
id.definition: A polyketide that is 4-hydroxypyran-2-one carrying an additional 4-(4-hydroxyphenyl)-2-oxobut-3-en-1-yl group at position 6; produced due to derailment from the canonical 2',4,4',6'-tetrahydroxychalcone-producing reaction pathway.

id.name: food additive carrier
id.definition: A food additive that is used to dilute, disperse or dissolve a food additive or nutrient without altering its function. Carriers are used to facilitate the handling or use of the food additive or nutrient.

id.name: hepoxilin B3(1-)
id.definition: A hepoxilin anion that is the conjugate base of hepoxilin B3, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: 1-hexanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A 1-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl group is specified as caproyl (hexanoyl).

id.name: 1,2-dioctanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as octanoyl.

id.name: oryzalexin A
id.definition: A tricyclic diterpenoid that is ent-sandaracopimaradiene bearing additional hydroxy and oxo substituents at the 3alpha- and 7-positions respectively.

id.name: ferruginol
id.definition: An abietane diterpenoid that is abieta-8,11,13-triene substituted by a hydroxy group at positions 12.

id.name: elloramycin A
id.definition: A member of the class of tetracenomycins that is 8-demethyltetracenomycin C in which the hydroxyl hydrogens at position 8 and 10 a are replaced by a 2,3,4-tri-O-methyl-alpha-L-rhamnosyl and methyl groups respectively.

id.name: carminic acid
id.definition: A tetrahydroxyanthraquinone that is that is 1,3,4,6-tetrahydroxy-9,10-anthraquinone substituted by a methyl group at position 8, a carboxy group at position 7 and a 1,5-anhydro-D-glucitol moiety at position 2 via a C-glycosidic linkage. It is a natural dye isolated from several insects such as Dactylopius coccus.

id.name: rac-ethyl lactate
id.definition: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-ethyl lactate.

id.name: fluorometholone acetate
id.definition: A steroid ester resulting from the formal condensation of the 17-hydroxy function of fluorometholone with acetic acid. Used in the treatment of steroid responsive inflammatory conditions of the palpebral and bulbar conjunctiva, cornea, and anterior segment of the eye.

id.name: chelerythrine
id.definition: A benzophenanthridine alkaloid isolated from the root of Zanthoxylum simulans, Chelidonium majus L., and other Papaveraceae.

id.name: guanosine 5'-[beta,gamma-imido]triphosphate
id.definition: A nucleoside triphosphate analogue that is GTP in which the oxygen atom bridging the beta- to the gamma- phosphate is replaced by a nitrogen atom A non-hydrolyzable analog of GTP, it binds tightly to G-protein in the presence of Mg(2+).

id.name: alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-[alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1-1')-N-acylsphingosine(2-)
id.definition: An anionic ganglioside obtained by deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of ganglioside GD1a; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: O-[S-(2E)-octenoylpantetheine-4-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue
id.definition: An O-(S-(2E)-enoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (2E)-octenoyl; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: 3'-(L-arginyl)adenylyl(1+) group
id.definition: An organic cationic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate function and protonation of the amino and guanidino functions of 3'-(L-arginyl)adenylyl group.

id.name: 11-dehydrocorticosterone
id.definition: An 11-oxo steroid that is corticosterone in which the hydroxy substituent at the 11beta position has been oxidised to give the corresponding ketone.

id.name: alpha-amino acid zwitterion
id.definition: An amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of any alpha-amino acid; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: N-hexadecanoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine
id.definition: A sphingomyelin 34:1 in which the N-acyl group and sphingoid base are specified as hexadecanoyl and sphingosine respectively.

id.name: O-[S-(2E)-2-enoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]-L-serine(1-) residue
id.definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue arising from deprotonation of the phosphate group of any O-[S-(2E)-enoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl]-L-serine residue; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: 4-terpineol
id.definition: A terpineol that is 1-menthene carrying a hydroxy substituent at position 4.

id.name: crocin-1
id.definition: A diester that is crocetin in which both of the carboxy groups have been converted to their gentiobiosyl esters. It is one of the water-soluble yellow-red pigments of saffron and is used as a spice for flavouring and colouring food. Note that in India, the term 'Crocin' is also used by GlaxoSmithKline as a brand-name for paracetamol.

id.name: selenoneine
id.definition: A histidine derivative that is N(alpha),N(alpha),N(alpha)-trimethyl-L-histidine substituted by a selenoxo group at position 2 on the imidazole ring. A selenium-containing antioxidant found in tuna blood.

id.name: 1,2-dioctanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate
id.definition: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as octanoyl.

id.name: EC 2.7.11.24 (mitogen-activated protein kinase) inhibitor
id.definition: An EC 2.7.11.* (protein-serine/threonine kinase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of mitogen-activated protein kinase (EC 2.7.11.24).

id.name: 2-hydroxy-7-methoxy-5-methyl-1-naphthoic acid
id.definition: A member of the class of naphthoic acids that is 1-naphthoic acid substituted at positions 2, 5 and 7 by hydroxy, methyl and methoxy groups respectively.

id.name: 1-(1Z-octadecenyl)-2-(9Z-octadecenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine
id.definition: A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alk-1-enyl and acyl groups are specified as (1Z)-octadecenyl and (9Z)-octadecenoyl respectively.

id.name: beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1-1)-ceramide
id.definition: Any glycodiaosylceramide having beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucose as the disaccharide component and undefined sphingoid base.

id.name: (3R,8R)-3,8-dihydroxynonanoic acid
id.definition: An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is (8R)-8-hydroxynonanoic acid in which the 3-pro-R hydrogen is replaced by a hydroxy group.

id.name: malonylgenistin
id.definition: A glycosyloxyisoflavone that is genistin in which the hydroxy hydrogen at position 6'' has been replaced by a malonyl group.

id.name: tauroursodeoxycholic acid
id.definition: A bile acid taurine conjugate derived from ursoodeoxycholic acid.

id.name: isolithocholic acid
id.definition: A monohydroxy-5beta-cholanic acid with a beta-hydroxy substituent at position 3. The 3beta-hydroxy epimer of lithocholic acid.

id.name: tebuconazole
id.definition: A racemate composed of equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-tebuconazole. A fungicide effective against various smut and bunt diseases in cereals and other field crops.

id.name: diflufenican
id.definition: A pyridinecarboxamide that is pyridine-3-carboxamide substituted by a 2,4-difluorophenyl group at the carbamoyl nitrogen and a 3-(trifluoromethyl)phenoxy group at position 2.

id.name: cuprous oxide
id.definition: Any copper oxide in which the metal is in the +1 oxidation state.

id.name: chlorotoluron
id.definition: A member of the class of phenylureas that is urea in which one of the nitrogens is substituted by two methyl groups while the other is substituted by a 3-chloro-4-methylphenyl group. A herbicide that is non-toxic to honeybees but moderately toxic to mammals, birds, earthworms and most aquatic organisms.

id.name: acid red 26
id.definition: An organic sodium salt that is the disodium salt of 4-[(2,4-dimethylphenyl)diazenyl]-3-hydroxynaphthalene-2,7-disulfonic acid. Its use is largely confined to Masson's trichrome, where it gives a slight orange shading to the red of the cytoplasmic structures.

id.name: Evans blue
id.definition: An organic sodium salt that is the tetrasodium salt of 6,6'-{(3,3'-dimethyl[1,1'-biphenyl]-4,4'-diyl)bis[diazene-2,1-diyl]}bis(4-amino-5-hydroxynaphthalene-1,3-disulfonate). It is sometimes used as a counterstain, especially in fluorescent methods to suppress background autofluorescence.

id.name: alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)-[beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1-1')-ceramide(1-)
id.definition: An anionic ganglioside that is the conjugate base alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)-[beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)]-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1-1')-ceramide arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: oritavancin
id.definition: A semisynthetic glycopeptide used (as its bisphosphate salt) for the treatment of acute bacterial skin and skin structure infections caused or suspected to be caused by susceptible isolates of designated Gram-positive microorganisms including MRSA.

id.name: N-acylhexadecasphingosine
id.definition: A ceramide consisting of an hexadecasphing-4-enine base having an unspecified fatty acyl group attached to the nitrogen.

id.name: 7alpha-hydroxy-3-oxo-4-cholestenoic acid
id.definition: A cholestanoid that is cholest-4-en-26-oic acid substituted by an alpha-hydroxy group at position 7 and an oxo group at position 3. It is an intermediate metabolite in the bile acid synthesis.

id.name: N-(hexadecanoyl)-beta-D-galactosylsphingosine
id.definition: A D-galactosyl-N-acylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as hexadecanoyl.

id.name: 4-dodecyl-2,6-dimethylmorpholine
id.definition: A member of the class of morpholines that is 2,6-dimethylmorpholine in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen is replaced by a dodecyl group. The configuration at positions 2 and 6 is unknown or unspecified.

id.name: orciprenaline sulfate
id.definition: A racemate composed of equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-orciprenaline sulfate. Used to relax the airway muscles and improve breathing for patients suffering from asthma or bronchitis.

id.name: N-lignoceroylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine
id.definition: A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as lignoceroyl (tetracosanoyl).

id.name: N-hexacosanoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine
id.definition: A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as hexacosanoyl.

id.name: O-(S-3-oxoicosanoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(1-) residue
id.definition: An O-(S-3-oxoacylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 3-oxoicosanoyl.

id.name: O-[S-(3R)-hydroxyicosanoylpantetheine-4-phosphoryl]serine(1-) residue
id.definition: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R)-hydroxyicosanoyl.

id.name: thifensulfuron-methyl
id.definition: A methyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of thifensulfuron with methanol. It is used as a post-emergence herbicide for the control of grass and broad-leaved weeds.

id.name: pendimethalin
id.definition: A member of the class of substituted anilines that is N-(pentan-3-yl)aniline bearing two additional nitro substituents at positions 2 and 6 as well as two methyl substituents at positions 3 and 4. A herbicide used to control most annual grasses and many annual broad-leaved weeds.

id.name: tribenuron
id.definition: An N-sulfonylurea that is N-(2-carboxybenzenesulfonyl)urea bearing additional methyl and 4-methoxy-6-methyl-1,3,5-triazin-2-yl substituents at position N3. A foliar acting, post-emergence herbicide used to control broad-leaved weeds in cereals, normally used as the methyl variant.

id.name: juvenile hormone I
id.definition: A member of the juvenile hormone family of compounds that is the methyl ester of methyl (2E,6E,10R,11S)-10,11-epoxy-7-ethyl-3,11-dimethyl-2,6-tridecanoic acid.

id.name: 3-oxo-23,24-bisnorchol-4-en-22-oyl-CoA(4-)
id.definition: An acyl-CoA oxoanion resulting from the removal of all four protons from the phosphate and diphosphate groups of 3-oxo-23,24-bisnor-chol-4-en-22-oyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: amino acid derivative
id.definition: Any derivative of an amino acid resulting from reaction at an amino group, carboxy group, side-chain functional group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen by a heteroatom. The definition normally excludes peptides containing amino acid residues.

id.name: 1-O-(1,2-saturated-alkyl)-sn-glycerol
id.definition: A 1-O-alkyl-sn-glycerol in which the alkyl group has a saturated bond between carbons 1 and 2.

id.name: 4-fluorophenylalanine
id.definition: A phenylalanine derivative in which the hydrogen at position 4 on the benzene ring is replaced by a fluoro group.

id.name: pentanal
id.definition: A saturated fatty aldehyde composed from five carbons in a straight chain.

id.name: quinmerac
id.definition: A quinolinemonocarboxylic acid that is quinoline-8-carboxylic acid carrying additional methyl and chloro substituents at positions 3 and 7 respectively. A residual herbicide used to control broad-leaved weeds on a range of crops including cereals, rape and beet.

id.name: 12-hydroxyoctadecanoate
id.definition: A hydroxy saturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 12-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: 1-stearoyl-2-(7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z-docosatetraenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine
id.definition: A 3-sn-phosphatidyl L-serine in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are stearoyl and 7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z-docosatetraenoyl respectively.

id.name: 1-[(9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl]-2-[(5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatetraenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A phosphatidylcholine 38:6 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl and (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatetraenoyl respectively.

id.name: 1-hexadecanoyl-2-[(7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatetraenoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A phosphatidylcholine 38:4 in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are hexadecanoyl and (7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatetraenoyl respectively.

id.name: beta-D-galactosyl-N-[(15Z)-tetracosenoyl]sphingosine
id.definition: A N-acyl-beta-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the acyl group is (15Z)-tetracosenoyl.

id.name: 2-deoxy-D-glucopyranose
id.definition: A 2-deoxy-D-glucose that is D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 2 has been replaced by a hydrogen.

id.name: 1-octadecanoyl-2-[(9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A phosphatidylcholine 36:2 in which the acyl groups positions 1 and 2 are specified as octadecanoyl and (9Z,12Z)-octadecadienoyl respectively.

id.name: 1-octadecanoyl-2-(4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z-docosahexaenoyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A phosphatidylcholine 40:6 in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are octadecanoyl and (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl respectively.

id.name: (R)-crotonylcarnitine
id.definition: A O-butenoyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group is specified as crotonyl.

id.name: ethyl (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoate
id.definition: A long-chain fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoic acid with the hydroxy group of ethanol.

id.name: trans,trans-2,4-dienoyl-CoA(4-)
id.definition: A 2,3-trans-enoyl CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of any trans,trans-2,4-dienoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: (9E)-12-(phosphonooxy)octadecenoic acid
id.definition: A carboxyalkyl phosphate that is (9E)-octadecenoic acid carrying a phosphonooxy substituent at position 12.

id.name: 9,10-dihydroxystearate
id.definition: A long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 9,10-dihydroxystearic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: peramivir
id.definition: A member of the class of guanidines that is used (as its trihydrate) for the treatment of acute uncomplicated influenza in patients 18 years and older who have been symptomatic for no more than two days.

id.name: 15-deoxy-Delta(12,14)-prostaglandin J2-2-glyceryl ester
id.definition: A 2-monoglyceride resulting from the condensation of the carboxy group of 15-deoxy-Delta(12,14)-prostaglandin J2 with the hydroxy group at position 2 of glycerol.

id.name: spiramycin I
id.definition: A macrolide antibiotic produced by various Streptomyces species that is used to treat toxoplasmosis and various other infections of soft tissues.

id.name: trans-4-hydroxy-L-proline betaine
id.definition: An amino-acid betaine that is trans-4-hydroxy-L-proline zwitterion in which both of the hydrogens attached to the nitrogen have been replaced by methyl groups.

id.name: N-hexadecenoylsphingosine-1-phosphocholine
id.definition: A sphingomyelin 34:2 in which the ceramide N-acyl group contains 16 carbons and 1 double bond.

id.name: sphingomyelin d18:1/18:1
id.definition: A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the fatty acyl group contains 16 carbons and 1 double bond

id.name: sphingomyelin 39:1
id.definition: A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 39 with 1 double bond.

id.name: (9Z,11E,13E,15Z)-octadecatetraenoyl group
id.definition: A parinaroyl group derived from (9Z,11E,13E,15Z)-octadecatetraenoic (alpha-parinaric) acid.

id.name: CMP-3-deoxy-beta-D-manno-octulosonic acid
id.definition: A CMP-sugar having 3-deoxy-beta-D-manno-octulosonic acid as the sugar component.

id.name: 6-bromoindirubin-3'-oxime
id.definition: A member of the class of biindoles that is indirubin substituted at position 6 by a bromo group and in which the keto group at position 3' has undergone condensation with hydroxylamine to form the corresponding oxime.

id.name: methyl sulfide
id.definition: Any aliphatic sulfide in which at least one of the organyl groups attached to the sulfur is a methyl group.

id.name: conazole antifungal agent
id.definition: A compound that has a structure that is related to miconazole, contains an azole (imidazole or triazole) moiety, and has significant systemic antifungal properties. They inhibit cytochrome P450-dependent enzymes (particularly C14-demethylase) involved in the biosynthesis of ergosterol, which is required for fungal cell membrane structure and function.

id.name: 5beta-dihydrocorticosterone
id.definition: A 3-oxo-5beta-steroid formed from corticosterone by reduction across the C4-C5 double bond.

id.name: 5beta-dihydroaldosterone
id.definition: A 3-oxo-5beta-steroid formed from aldosterone by reduction across the C4-C5 double bond.

id.name: fortimicin KK1
id.definition: An amino cyclitol glycoside that is (1R,2S,3S,4S,5S,6R)-2-amino-1,3,4,6-tetrahydroxy-5-(methylamino)cyclohexane in which the hydroxy group at position 1 is glycosylated by a heptapyranosyl residue.

id.name: potassium aluminium sulfate dodecahydrate
id.definition: A hydrate resulting from the the formal combination of anhydrous potassium aluminium sulfate with 12 mol eq. of water.

id.name: GDP-4-dehydro-beta-L-fucose
id.definition: A GDP-4-dehydro-L-fucose in which the anomeric centre of the fucose portion has beta-configuration. An intermediate formed during the de novo synthesis of GDP-L-fucose.

id.name: 2-hydroxyethyl salicylate
id.definition: A benzoate ester obtained by the formal condensation of carboxy group of salicylic acid with one of the hydroxy groups of ethylene glycol

id.name: buddlenol B
id.definition: A guaiacyl lignin that is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.

id.name: buddlenol C
id.definition: A guaiacyl lignin that is syringaresinol in which one of the phenolic hydrogens is replaced by a guaiacylglycerol group. It is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.

id.name: simulanol
id.definition: A guaiacyl lignin that is found in Arabidopsis thaliana.

id.name: 4,4-dimethyl-5alpha-cholest-8-en-3beta-ol
id.definition: A cholestanoid that is 5alpha-cholesta-8-en-3beta-ol bearing two additional methyl substituents at position 4.

id.name: acid green 5
id.definition: An organic sodium salt having 3-[(ethyl{4-[(4-{ethyl[(3-sulfonatophenyl)methyl]amino}phenyl)(4-sulfonatophenyl)methylidene]cyclohexa-2,5-dien-1-ylidene}azaniumyl)methyl]benzene-1-sulfonate as the counterion. It is the standard dye in North American for staining collagen and is also used extensively in plant histology.

id.name: 1-ethoxy-1-pentoxyethane
id.definition: A dieter that is 1-pentoxyethane substituted by an ethoxy group at position 1.

id.name: hexan-1-ol
id.definition: A primary alcohol that is hexane substituted by a hydroxy group at position 1.

id.name: UK 63598
id.definition: A cyclodepsipeptide antibiotic that is isolated from Streptomyces sp. SNA15896 and also exhibits antitumour activity.

id.name: ethyl octanoate
id.definition: A fatty acid ethyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of octanoic acid with ethanol.

id.name: rosanilin
id.definition: A hydrochloride that is the monohydrochloride of 4-[(4-aminophenyl)(4-iminocyclohexa-2,5-dien-1-ylidene)methyl]-2-methylaniline. One of the major constituents of Basic fuchsin, together with pararosanilin, magenta II and new fuchsin.

id.name: (R)-warfarin
id.definition: A 4-hydroxy-3-(3-oxo-1-phenylbutyl)-2H-1-benzopyran-2-one that has (R)-configuration (the racemate is warfarin, an anticoagulant drug and rodenticide).

id.name: (S)-warfarin
id.definition: A 4-hydroxy-3-(3-oxo-1-phenylbutyl)-2H-1-benzopyran-2-one that has (S)-configuration (the racemate is warfarin, an anticoagulant drug and rodenticide).

id.name: pentan-3-one
id.definition: A pentanone that is pentane carrying an oxo group at position 3. It has been isolated from Triatoma brasiliensis and Triatoma infestans.

id.name: 4,6-dioxoheptanoic acid
id.definition: A dioxo monocarboxylic acid that is heptanoic acid in which oxo groups replace the hydrogens at positions 4 and 6. It is an abnormal metabolite of the tyrosine metabolic pathway and a marker for type 1 tyrosinaemia.

id.name: Sudan IV
id.definition: A bis(azo) compound that is 2-naphthol substituted at position 1 by a {2-methyl-4-[(2-methylphenyl)diazenyl]phenyl}diazenyl group. A fat-soluble dye predominantly used for demonstrating triglycerides in frozen sections, but which may also stain some protein bound lipids in paraffin sections.

id.name: 3beta,7alpha-dihydroxy-5beta-cholan-24-oic acid
id.definition: A dihydroxy-5beta-cholanic acid in which the two hydroxy groups are located at positions 3beta and 7alpha. The 3beta-hydroxy epimer of chenodeoxycholic acid.

id.name: (S)-2-methyl-1-(4-methylisoquinoline-5-sulfonyl)-1,4-diazepane
id.definition: A member of the class of isoquinolines that is the sulfonamide formed by the formal condensation of the sulfo group of 4-methylisoquinoline-5-sulfonic acid with the 1-amino group of (S)-2-methyl-1,4-diazepane.

id.name: beta-Gal-(1->3)-beta-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-Gal-(1->4)-beta-Glc-(1-1')-Cer(d18:1/18:0)(2-)
id.definition: An anionic ganglioside obtained by deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of ganglioside GD1b(d18:1/C18:0); major species at pH 7.3.

id.name: linoleoyl-containing glycerolipid
id.definition: A glycerolipid where one of the acyl groups is specified as linoleoyl

id.name: coprostanol
id.definition: A member of the class of phytosterols that is 5beta-cholestane carrying a hydroxy substituent at the 3beta-position.

id.name: 1-oleoyl-2-[(8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoyl]-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine
id.definition: A phosphatidylcholine 38:4 in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as oleoyl and (8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoyl respectively.

id.name: (S)-2-methylbutanoyl-CoA
id.definition: A (2S)-2-methylacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (2S)-2-methylbutanoic acid.

id.name: 11beta,13-dihydrolactucin
id.definition: A sesquiterpene lactone obtained by formal hydrogenation across the 11,13-double bond of lactucin. Found in chicory

id.name: N-(indol-3-ylacetyl)glycine
id.definition: An N-acylglycine in which the N-acyl group is specified as indol-3-ylacetyl.

id.name: dibenzothiophene sulfone
id.definition: A sulfone resulting from the oxidation of the sulfur atom of dibenzothiophene.

id.name: S-(5-deoxy-beta-D-ribos-5-yl)-L-homocysteine
id.definition: An S-(5-deoxy-D-ribos-5-yl)-L-homocysteine in which the anomeric centre has beta-configuration.

id.name: succinic acid-d4
id.definition: A deuterated compound that is succinic acid in which the four methylene hydrogens are replaced by deuterium.

id.name: phosphatidylserine(18:1/22:1)
id.definition: A 3-sn-phosphatidyl-L-serine in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are octadecenoyl and docosenoyl respectively.

id.name: O-(chloroacetylcarbamoyl)fumagillol
id.definition: A carbamate ester that is fumagillol in which the hydroxy group has been converted to the corresponding N-(chloroacetyl)carbamate derivative.

id.name: antidote to organophosphate poisoning
id.definition: A role borne by a molecule that acts to counteract or neutralise the deleterious effects of organophosphates or acetylcholinesterase inhibitors (nerve agents).

id.name: 5-[(E)-caffeoyl]shikimate
id.definition: A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 5-[(E)-caffeoyl]shikimic acid. Major structure at pH 7.3

id.name: epithienamycin E
id.definition: A member of the class of carbapenems that is (5R,6R)-3-{[(E)-2-aminoethenyl]sulfanyl}-6-[(1S)-1-hydroxyethyl]-7-oxo-1-azabicyclo[3.2.0]hept-2-ene-2-carboxylic acid in which the free hydroxy and amino groups are carrying sulfo and acetyl substituents respectively.

id.name: guaiacylglycerol beta-coniferyl ether
id.definition: A guaiacyl lignin that is guaiacylglycerol in which the hydrogen on the 2-hydroxy function has been replaced by a beta-coniferyl group.

id.name: dehydrodiconiferyl alcohol
id.definition: A guaiacyl lignin obtained by cyclodimerisation of coniferol.

id.name: AZD-8055
id.definition: A pyridopyrimidine that is pyrido[2,3-d]pyrimidine which is substituted at positions 2 and 4 by (3S)-3-methylmorpholin-4-yl groups and at position 5 by a 3-(hydroxymethyl)-4-methoxyphenyl group. It is an mTOR complex 1/2 (mTORC1/2) dual inhibitor [mTOR = mammalian target of rapamycin].

id.name: SU6656
id.definition: A member of the class of oxindoles that is 3-methyleneoxindole in which the hydrogeh at position 5 has been replaced by a dimethylaminosulfonyl group and in which one of the hydrogens of the methylene group has been replaced by a 4,5,6,7-tetrahydro-indol-2-yl group. It is a specific inhibitor of Src family kinase.

id.name: 1-(2-methylphenyl)glycerol
id.definition: A glycerol ether in which a single 2-methylphenyl group is attached at position 1 of glycerol via an ether linkage.

id.name: nalidixic acid
id.definition: A monocarboxylic acid comprising 1,8-naphthyridin-4-one substituted by carboxylic acid, ethyl and methyl groups at positions 3, 1, and 7, respectively. An orally administered antibacterial, it is used in the treatment of lower urinary-tract infections due to Gram-negative bacteria, including the majority of E. coli, Enterobacter, Klebsiella, and Proteus species.

id.name: ciprofloxacin
id.definition: A quinolone that is quinolin-4(1H)-one bearing cyclopropyl, carboxylic acid, fluoro and piperazin-1-yl substituents at positions 1, 3, 6 and 7, respectively.

id.name: norfloxacin
id.definition: A quinolinemonocarboxylic acid with broad-spectrum antibacterial activity against most gram-negative and gram-positive bacteria. Norfloxacin is bactericidal and its mode of action depends on blocking of bacterial DNA replication by binding itself to an enzyme called DNA gyrase.

id.name: diclofenamide
id.definition: A sulfonamide that is benzene-1,3-disulfonamide in which the hydrogens at positions 4 and 5 are substituted by chlorine. An oral carbonic anhydrase inhibitor, it partially suppresses the secretion (inflow) of aqueous humor in the eye and so reduces intraocular pressure. It is used for the treatment of glaucoma.

id.name: diltiazem
id.definition: A 5-[2-(dimethylamino)ethyl]-2-(4-methoxyphenyl)-4-oxo-2,3,4,5-tetrahydro-1,5-benzothiazepin-3-yl acetate in which both stereocentres have S configuration. A calcium-channel blocker and vasodilator, it is used as the hydrochloride in the management of angina pectoris and hypertension.

id.name: sorbinil
id.definition: An azaspiro compound having a monofluoro-substituted chromane skeleton spiro-linked to an imidazolidinedione ring.

id.name: thiopental
id.definition: A barbiturate, the structure of which is that of 2-thiobarbituric acid substituted at C-5 by ethyl and sec-pentyl groups.

id.name: methohexital
id.definition: A barbiturate, the structure of which is that of barbituric acid substituted at N-1 by a methyl group and at C-5 by allyl and 1-methylpent-2-ynyl groups.

id.name: sulfisoxazole
id.definition: A sulfonamide antibacterial with an oxazole substituent. It has antibiotic activity against a wide range of gram-negative and gram-positive organisms.

id.name: p-aminohippuric acid
id.definition: An N-acylglycine that is the 4-amino derivative of hippuric acid; used as a diagnostic agent in the measurement of renal plasma flow.

id.name: rolipram
id.definition: A member of the lclass of pyrrolidin-2-ones that is pyrrolidin-2-one bearing a 3-(cyclopentyloxy)-4-methoxyphenyl substituent at the 4-position. It is a type IV-specific phosphodiesterase (PDE4) inhibitor.

id.name: (S)-famoxadone
id.definition: A 5-methyl-5-(4-phenoxyphenyl)-3-(phenylamino)-1,3-oxazolidine-2,4-dione that is the (active) (S)-enantiomer of famoxadone. It prevents spore germination and mycelial growth of sensitive fungi and is used in agriculture for the control of various fungal diseases.

id.name: metoclopramide
id.definition: A member of the class of benzamides resulting from the formal condensation of 4-amino-5-chloro-2-methoxybenzoic acid with the primary amino group of N,N-diethylethane-1,2-diamine.

id.name: 1-hexadecanoyl-2-[(9Z)-hexadecenoyl]-3-[(9Z)-octadecenoyl]-sn-glycerol
